1
00:00:06,506 --> 00:00:09,175
Oh, I'm a guest who…
who got here a little late.

2
00:00:09,259 --> 00:00:10,552
Can I come in now?

3
00:00:11,469 --> 00:00:14,055
<i>You've got the red carpet</i>
<i>rolled out for us, right?</i>

4
00:00:14,139 --> 00:00:15,306
Who is this?

5
00:00:15,390 --> 00:00:16,558
It's Hyo-ri.

6
00:00:16,641 --> 00:00:18,518
What? Who is it?

7
00:00:19,269 --> 00:00:21,021
Well, I just got here.

8
00:00:21,104 --> 00:00:22,313
Where are you?

9
00:00:22,939 --> 00:00:24,107
Where?

10
00:00:24,691 --> 00:00:26,276
Where?

11
00:00:26,359 --> 00:00:27,861
- Is this for real?
- Wait, really? Hello?

12
00:00:27,944 --> 00:00:29,320
Hey, <i>oppa</i>.

13
00:00:29,404 --> 00:00:30,780
Hey, Hyo-ri. Where are you?

14
00:00:31,281 --> 00:00:34,034
- I don't know. I'm in some parking lot.
- Where is she?

15
00:00:34,117 --> 00:00:36,286
- I'll come pick you up.
- We're coming. Hold on.

16
00:00:36,369 --> 00:00:37,829
I'm expecting a limo.

17
00:00:37,912 --> 00:00:39,080
<i>Okay. Okay, got it.</i>

18
00:00:39,164 --> 00:00:40,707
Whoa, I can't believe this.

19
00:00:40,790 --> 00:00:42,042
- I'm a huge fan.
- Seriously?

20
00:00:42,125 --> 00:00:43,585
Was that really Lee Hyo-ri?

21
00:00:44,085 --> 00:00:45,086
I think it was.

22
00:00:45,795 --> 00:00:46,838
No way.

23
00:00:46,921 --> 00:00:49,132
- I gotta see this.
- It was for sure her voice.

24
00:00:49,215 --> 00:00:51,468
- Yeah, it was definitely her voice.
- Come on. Let's go.

25
00:00:51,551 --> 00:00:52,552
We have to go see her.

26
00:00:52,635 --> 00:00:54,012
- Absolutely.
- Let's go.

27
00:00:54,095 --> 00:00:55,555
- Absolutely.
- Come on.

28
00:00:56,139 --> 00:00:58,683
SWARMING

29
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:00,268
She wants a limo and a red carpet.

30
00:01:00,351 --> 00:01:01,895
- Let's go find one.
- Seriously?

31
00:01:01,978 --> 00:01:04,814
- No, stay there. Stay there.
- Stay there.

32
00:01:04,898 --> 00:01:06,566
Everyone, remain calm!

33
00:01:06,649 --> 00:01:08,193
- Hang on a sec.
- What do we do?

34
00:01:08,276 --> 00:01:09,944
- Should I stay here?
- Yeah. Wait here.

35
00:01:10,028 --> 00:01:11,279
Okay.

36
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:13,698
WOO-SEOK MISSED IT ALL
WHILE HE WAS IN THE BATHROOM

37
00:01:13,782 --> 00:01:16,284
I can't believe she's actually
coming. She was asking for a limo.

38
00:01:16,367 --> 00:01:17,786
Let's go find a red carpet.

39
00:01:17,869 --> 00:01:19,913
(WHAT'S THE FUSS ABOUT?)

40
00:01:20,497 --> 00:01:22,665
<i>Oppa</i>! Hyo-ri is coming.

41
00:01:22,749 --> 00:01:24,709
- Wait, really?
- Isn't that amazing?

42
00:01:25,293 --> 00:01:26,377
Hyo-ri's here?

43
00:01:27,462 --> 00:01:28,671
Is this for real?

44
00:01:28,755 --> 00:01:29,964
Is she really here?

45
00:01:31,299 --> 00:01:32,759
Wow. This is huge.

46
00:01:32,842 --> 00:01:34,344
WE'RE COMING TO PICK YOU UP

47
00:01:34,427 --> 00:01:36,012
Can she cook?

48
00:01:36,096 --> 00:01:37,931
Hyo-ri is a good cook.

49
00:01:38,014 --> 00:01:39,015
This is great.

50
00:01:39,099 --> 00:01:41,017
The plan for dinner wasn't even
decided on yet,

51
00:01:41,101 --> 00:01:42,185
- so maybe…
- Oh, yeah.

52
00:01:42,685 --> 00:01:44,479
- I didn't even think about that.
- This is awesome.

53
00:01:44,562 --> 00:01:45,522
It'll be great.

54
00:01:45,605 --> 00:01:47,774
- We were out of ideas.
- Yeah, I know.

55
00:01:48,358 --> 00:01:49,567
Amazing. Look there.

56
00:01:49,651 --> 00:01:50,693
Isn't that her?

57
00:01:50,777 --> 00:01:53,113
- We need to go around here.
- Wait, hold on.

58
00:01:53,196 --> 00:01:54,948
- Is Sang-soon with her?
- She came with Sang-soon.

59
00:01:56,366 --> 00:01:57,367
Here they come.

60
00:01:57,450 --> 00:01:59,536
- What? You're actually here.
- Hey, guys!

61
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:00,954
- Hey, Sang-soon.
- Hello.

62
00:02:01,538 --> 00:02:02,872
HYO-RI AND SANG-SOON
DOUBLE THE JOY

63
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:04,541
- Gosh! What's going on?
- Hi there.

64
00:02:04,624 --> 00:02:06,376
- Hey.
- Wow, this is crazy.

65
00:02:06,459 --> 00:02:07,919
- Kwang-soo.
- How have you been?

66
00:02:08,002 --> 00:02:10,255
- What's with the bling?
- Oh, it's for something I'm filming.

67
00:02:10,338 --> 00:02:11,798
You've changed a lot, Kwang-soo.

68
00:02:11,881 --> 00:02:13,758
- You've changed a lot.
- It's great to see you.

69
00:02:13,842 --> 00:02:14,843
Director Lee.

70
00:02:14,926 --> 00:02:15,844
- I'm sorry but…
- Welcome.

71
00:02:15,927 --> 00:02:18,221
…you can't even handle
one show on your own?

72
00:02:18,304 --> 00:02:20,682
- Wait.
- Do I really have to come and help you?

73
00:02:20,765 --> 00:02:22,058
Hey, Sang-soon!

74
00:02:22,142 --> 00:02:24,102
- This is great.
- I'm so happy to see you.

75
00:02:25,311 --> 00:02:26,896
I was really surprised.

76
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:28,022
They actually came.

77
00:02:28,106 --> 00:02:31,234
Sang-soon and Hyo-ri
are basically the originals,

78
00:02:31,317 --> 00:02:33,444
the pioneers of B&B variety shows.

79
00:02:34,070 --> 00:02:38,032
So their experience and know-how
really give me something to lean on.

80
00:02:38,116 --> 00:02:40,285
Having them here makes me feel reassured.

81
00:02:40,368 --> 00:02:42,662
All right, get in. For real, we gotta go.

82
00:02:42,745 --> 00:02:44,831
- This is great.
- I'm so glad you guys are here.

83
00:02:44,914 --> 00:02:46,916
- Did you need us that badly?
- What do you need?

84
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,042
Well, the thing is…

85
00:02:48,626 --> 00:02:50,670
we just made kimchi fried rice for lunch,

86
00:02:50,753 --> 00:02:53,923
and now we've got to start working
on dinner which is coming up soon.

87
00:02:54,424 --> 00:02:56,718
We were like, "Man,
what should we even make this time?"

88
00:02:56,801 --> 00:02:58,052
Well, <i>oppa</i>'s good at cooking, so…

89
00:02:58,136 --> 00:02:59,762
I'm actually not.

90
00:02:59,846 --> 00:03:02,223
I meant Sang-soon. He's good.

91
00:03:02,307 --> 00:03:04,934
That's right. Sang-soon's good,
and so are you, Hyo-ri.

92
00:03:05,018 --> 00:03:06,644
So what is this exactly?

93
00:03:06,728 --> 00:03:08,146
- It's not a guesthouse, right?
- No.

94
00:03:08,229 --> 00:03:09,689
- What are we doing here?
- Well…

95
00:03:09,772 --> 00:03:10,607
It's a B&B.

96
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:12,025
- A B&B?
- Uh-huh.

97
00:03:12,108 --> 00:03:14,235
- Like some kind of retreat?
- Yeah, something like that.

98
00:03:14,319 --> 00:03:15,612
- Oh.
- So, at the moment,

99
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:17,780
we have about 20 guests staying with us.

100
00:03:17,864 --> 00:03:19,574
- Twenty?
- Twenty, that's a lot.

101
00:03:19,657 --> 00:03:21,034
How do you cook for all of them?

102
00:03:21,117 --> 00:03:22,702
- That's kinda where we--
- That's actually

103
00:03:22,785 --> 00:03:24,120
- our biggest problem.
- Our biggest struggle.

104
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:26,372
- It's not just the two of you, right?
- No, there's Woo-seok too.

105
00:03:26,456 --> 00:03:27,874
- Woo-seok and Ye-eun are here.
- Ye-eun?

106
00:03:27,957 --> 00:03:29,417
And they can't cook either?

107
00:03:30,043 --> 00:03:31,085
- They're hopeless.
- No.

108
00:03:31,169 --> 00:03:33,379
- Too salty! Too salty!
- Oh, it's out.

109
00:03:33,463 --> 00:03:35,757
- We're all out of ideas.
- Basically, that part's been a mess.

110
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:36,925
Just get delivery.

111
00:03:37,508 --> 00:03:38,676
Well, we could, but still,

112
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,595
- that wouldn't be right.
- I see. You want to cook everything

113
00:03:40,678 --> 00:03:42,055
- for them yourselves.
- Think about it.

114
00:03:42,138 --> 00:03:42,972
Of course.

115
00:03:43,056 --> 00:03:45,308
Wow, this is really awesome.

116
00:03:45,391 --> 00:03:46,309
OFF TO THE B&B

117
00:03:46,392 --> 00:03:47,560
When did you get here?

118
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:49,187
- This morning.
- This morning?

119
00:03:49,270 --> 00:03:50,605
This isn't your first shoot though, right?

120
00:03:50,688 --> 00:03:51,773
- Right, it's--
- It's our second.

121
00:03:51,856 --> 00:03:53,650
- Oh.
- We already had our first group of guests

122
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:55,401
- stay with us last month.
- The first's already come and gone.

123
00:03:55,485 --> 00:03:57,612
- This is the second group.
- Was the first group fun?

124
00:03:57,695 --> 00:03:59,072
- It was fun.
- Really fun.

125
00:03:59,155 --> 00:04:01,241
- I heard a rumor that you lost your voice.
- That's true.

126
00:04:01,324 --> 00:04:02,700
- What did you do?
- Wait, how?

127
00:04:02,784 --> 00:04:03,660
- What goes on here?
- Yeah.

128
00:04:03,743 --> 00:04:04,661
All kinds of things.

129
00:04:04,744 --> 00:04:05,745
Well, we did a quiz and…

130
00:04:05,828 --> 00:04:06,663
YOU SEE, AT OUR B&B…

131
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:07,580
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

132
00:04:07,664 --> 00:04:09,082
THEY WILL BE PLAYING HARD

133
00:04:09,165 --> 00:04:10,333
- Whoa!
- Whoa!

134
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,293
Check it out.

135
00:04:12,377 --> 00:04:13,253
MESSING AROUND

136
00:04:14,462 --> 00:04:15,964
…a talent show type thing.

137
00:04:17,006 --> 00:04:17,882
AND TALKING NONSTOP

138
00:04:17,966 --> 00:04:20,134
Whoa, where did that come from?

139
00:04:20,218 --> 00:04:21,678
So they're not here to rest.

140
00:04:21,761 --> 00:04:23,680
- Who, these people?
- Yeah.

141
00:04:23,763 --> 00:04:25,473
They're not the kind to sit around
all day doing nothing.

142
00:04:25,556 --> 00:04:26,683
So, they're like that then.

143
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:27,642
THIS IS A B&B WHERE YOU'RE FREE

144
00:04:27,725 --> 00:04:28,935
TO TALK NONSTOP,
PLAY HARD, AND MESS AROUND

145
00:04:29,018 --> 00:04:31,062
PLEASE NOTE IT'S VERY DIFFERENT
FROM <i>HYORI'S BED & BREAKFAST</i>

146
00:04:31,145 --> 00:04:33,856
You know, our Bed & Breakfast
was more about relaxing and recharging.

147
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:37,110
Well, here, people are always asking,
"Hey, aren't we going to do something?"

148
00:04:37,193 --> 00:04:38,486
Look, see? They're already outside.

149
00:04:38,569 --> 00:04:40,154
- Is that them?
- They're so excited.

150
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:41,447
They heard you were coming.

151
00:04:41,531 --> 00:04:42,949
They heard your voice on the phone.

152
00:04:43,032 --> 00:04:44,659
- They're going crazy right now.
- They're back!

153
00:04:44,742 --> 00:04:46,411
- They're back, they're back.
- Oh!

154
00:04:46,494 --> 00:04:48,454
Oh, Lee Sang-soon came with her?

155
00:04:48,538 --> 00:04:50,206
- You're right!
- They came together?

156
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:51,207
No way.

157
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:53,126
- It's really Lee Hyo-ri.
- So cool.

158
00:04:53,209 --> 00:04:54,669
- The two of them came together.
- Really?

159
00:04:54,752 --> 00:04:57,338
- Lee Sang-soon too? Crazy!
- Yeah, it looks like they're both here.

160
00:04:57,422 --> 00:04:59,465
All right, Lee Hyo-ri
and Sang-soon are here!

161
00:05:03,094 --> 00:05:05,805
MASSIVE CHEERS

162
00:05:05,888 --> 00:05:08,474
What are they all doing
standing around out here?

163
00:05:08,558 --> 00:05:09,642
They all just ran out.

164
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:11,811
Oh, my gosh. This is crazy!

165
00:05:11,894 --> 00:05:12,895
Oh, my gosh.

166
00:05:12,979 --> 00:05:14,897
Ah, they were all inside before?

167
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:15,982
There's Woo-seok.

168
00:05:16,065 --> 00:05:17,692
Hello, <i>sunbae</i>. I'm Byeon Woo-seok.

169
00:05:17,775 --> 00:05:19,360
- Nice to meet you.
- Oh, my gosh!

170
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:20,903
- Hello, <i>sunbae</i>. I'm Byeon Woo-seok.
- Oh, my gosh.

171
00:05:20,987 --> 00:05:21,988
Nice to meet you.

172
00:05:22,071 --> 00:05:24,407
- Nice to meet you.
- How're you doing?

173
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:25,616
- Nice to meet you.
- How're you doing?

174
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:26,534
- Hey, Hyo-ri.
- What?

175
00:05:26,617 --> 00:05:27,785
- Hi, there.
- Oh, Ye-eun!

176
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:30,079
Hello! I'm such a huge fan.

177
00:05:30,830 --> 00:05:33,333
- You were happy to see Woo-seok, right?
- Yes. Yes, of course.

178
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:35,126
I'm just happy that she's happy.

179
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:37,628
- Hello.
- Hello.

180
00:05:37,712 --> 00:05:39,380
- Hi, lovely to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

181
00:05:39,464 --> 00:05:40,340
ALMOST LIKE A FAN MEETING

182
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:43,134
Meeting Lee Hyo-ri
in person was so special.

183
00:05:43,217 --> 00:05:44,886
I could really feel her aura.

184
00:05:45,678 --> 00:05:47,472
I'm a fan of Lee Hyo-ri's.

185
00:05:47,555 --> 00:05:49,640
I've liked her since high school.

186
00:05:49,724 --> 00:05:52,268
I thought,
"I see what this show is about."

187
00:05:52,894 --> 00:05:54,604
- Nice to meet you.
- Hello.

188
00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:56,356
- Nice to meet all you.
- I'm such a fan.

189
00:05:56,439 --> 00:05:57,440
So great to meet you.

190
00:05:57,523 --> 00:05:58,441
(HOP, HOP)

191
00:05:58,524 --> 00:06:02,028
You should have seen them earlier.
We didn't get that kind of reaction.

192
00:06:02,987 --> 00:06:04,572
THREE HOURS EARLIER,
AT ORIENTATION

193
00:06:05,573 --> 00:06:07,700
THREE HOURS AFTER CHECK-IN,
BRYAN'S FINALLY SMILING BRIGHTLY

194
00:06:07,784 --> 00:06:10,912
To meet the celebrity of celebrities
was amazing.

195
00:06:11,913 --> 00:06:14,624
I was shocked.
I was like "How is this real?"

196
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:16,417
EVEN THE CALM NAM-JIN

197
00:06:17,418 --> 00:06:19,504
IS ALL SMILES

198
00:06:19,587 --> 00:06:21,130
- Hello.
- So glad to meet you!

199
00:06:21,214 --> 00:06:23,007
- All right, these are…
- Yeah.

200
00:06:23,091 --> 00:06:24,675
These are all our guests here,

201
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:26,219
- as you already know.
- Right.

202
00:06:26,302 --> 00:06:29,347
They were told not to share
their jobs or ages with each other yet.

203
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:31,099
Oh, kind of like <i>I am SOLO</i>?

204
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:34,602
- Well, it's a little different from that.
- No, not like <i>I am SOLO</i>.

205
00:06:34,685 --> 00:06:35,686
Why aren't they telling that?

206
00:06:35,770 --> 00:06:37,647
Well, you know, it's kind of…
How should I explain?

207
00:06:37,730 --> 00:06:40,233
- Some of them don't wanna share that yet.
- Some people don't want to reveal that.

208
00:06:40,316 --> 00:06:41,776
- Oh.
- To avoid stereotyping.

209
00:06:41,859 --> 00:06:42,693
That's right.

210
00:06:42,777 --> 00:06:44,529
<i>Oppa</i>, say hi. Why are you lurking?

211
00:06:44,612 --> 00:06:45,530
- Yeah, Sang-soon.
- Hello.

212
00:06:45,613 --> 00:06:47,407
- Hello.
- Hi!

213
00:06:47,490 --> 00:06:48,324
WE WELCOME YOU TOO,
MR. SANG-SOON

214
00:06:48,408 --> 00:06:49,409
I was just waiting.

215
00:06:49,492 --> 00:06:50,910
This was a surprise for me as well.

216
00:06:50,993 --> 00:06:53,121
I only found out today
that Sang-soon and Hyo-ri were coming.

217
00:06:53,204 --> 00:06:54,080
Seriously.

218
00:06:54,163 --> 00:06:56,249
I'm guessing the two of them
will be staff, just like us.

219
00:06:56,332 --> 00:06:57,166
Oh!

220
00:06:57,250 --> 00:07:00,420
I mean, I sure hope they'll help us out
with their expertise.

221
00:07:00,503 --> 00:07:03,381
- Staff? That doesn't really suit us.
- What would you prefer?

222
00:07:03,464 --> 00:07:05,425
How about landlords?

223
00:07:05,508 --> 00:07:06,342
Okay.

224
00:07:06,426 --> 00:07:07,844
- But he's the owner.
- Yeah.

225
00:07:07,927 --> 00:07:10,179
- Let's say you're the founders.
- Make yourselves at home.

226
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:11,389
Let's go with that.

227
00:07:11,472 --> 00:07:13,349
Think of them as the founders.

228
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:15,309
All right, well,
introductions are done, so…

229
00:07:15,393 --> 00:07:16,477
You have free time.

230
00:07:16,561 --> 00:07:18,563
So they can do anything right now?

231
00:07:18,646 --> 00:07:20,690
- It's free time.
- Yeah. We just ate, <i>nuna</i>.

232
00:07:20,773 --> 00:07:22,191
Oh. Gotcha.

233
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:23,484
And in here…

234
00:07:23,568 --> 00:07:24,944
- Wow.
- They all get one of these.

235
00:07:25,027 --> 00:07:26,654
- They sleep here together?
- They sleep here?

236
00:07:26,737 --> 00:07:27,905
- Exactly.
- They each have their own bed.

237
00:07:27,989 --> 00:07:31,409
This must be a really fresh
and new experience for the guests.

238
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:33,953
This is…

239
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:35,997
We all sleep here together?

240
00:07:36,747 --> 00:07:39,459
This is for the guys.
Ye-eun's in the other room by herself.

241
00:07:39,542 --> 00:07:41,127
I need to sleep with my husband.

242
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:43,671
What did you say?

243
00:07:43,754 --> 00:07:45,381
We're married.
How can we sleep separately?

244
00:07:45,465 --> 00:07:46,924
- She's right.
- Oh, really?

245
00:07:47,008 --> 00:07:48,384
- Yeah.
- She's right.

246
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:51,095
- Uh, in that case…
- We'll just use this room then.

247
00:07:51,179 --> 00:07:52,472
- The big room?
- Yeah.

248
00:07:52,555 --> 00:07:54,432
Well, you're married,
so I guess that makes sense.

249
00:07:54,515 --> 00:07:56,017
Maybe we decide on that later.

250
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:56,934
Yeah, later.

251
00:07:57,018 --> 00:07:59,020
- You can unpack first. Later, we'll…
- Yeah, sure.

252
00:08:01,647 --> 00:08:04,317
So there's nothing we're supposed
to do or anything? We just…

253
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:06,027
We do one activity per day.

254
00:08:06,110 --> 00:08:07,445
And what's today's activity?

255
00:08:07,528 --> 00:08:09,864
Today, uh, we're going to do
a special quiz later.

256
00:08:09,947 --> 00:08:11,741
- Oh, yeah? A quiz?
- A quiz?

257
00:08:11,824 --> 00:08:13,201
You know the cushion quiz from my show?

258
00:08:13,284 --> 00:08:14,368
- Yeah.
- We're gonna do that.

259
00:08:14,452 --> 00:08:17,121
But it's just one night here,
so it's pretty short, right?

260
00:08:17,205 --> 00:08:18,498
It's two nights, three days.

261
00:08:18,581 --> 00:08:19,916
Two nights and three days?

262
00:08:19,999 --> 00:08:22,418
- Yeah, two nights, three days.
- So we're the only ones staying one night.

263
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:23,503
- You leave tomorrow?
- Yeah.

264
00:08:23,586 --> 00:08:24,420
What time?

265
00:08:24,962 --> 00:08:27,840
- Well, after lunch I guess.
- Probably… Yeah, we should go.

266
00:08:28,341 --> 00:08:30,092
Can't you stay for two nights?

267
00:08:30,176 --> 00:08:31,761
- Would you like us to?
- Of course.

268
00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:33,387
You heard him!

269
00:08:33,471 --> 00:08:34,889
Did you see the look in his eyes?

270
00:08:34,972 --> 00:08:37,141
- Are you kidding?
- He was so earnest.

271
00:08:37,225 --> 00:08:38,559
"Can't you stay for two?"

272
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:41,020
I haven't heard you speak
that gently in a while!

273
00:08:41,103 --> 00:08:43,731
"Would you like us to?" What was that?

274
00:08:43,814 --> 00:08:46,609
It just feels like we have
someone who understands now.

275
00:08:47,193 --> 00:08:49,237
Well, since you're here…
we'd love the help.

276
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:51,989
Sang-soon, you brought
the old six-string with you, right?

277
00:08:52,073 --> 00:08:53,574
"Six-string."

278
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:55,368
Are we having a campfire?

279
00:08:55,451 --> 00:08:57,203
- That'd be good for the evening.
- A campfire? Sure.

280
00:08:57,286 --> 00:08:58,788
Oh, Hyo-ri's into yoga, right?

281
00:08:58,871 --> 00:09:00,790
- Should I do a class?
- You can do it in the morning.

282
00:09:00,873 --> 00:09:02,667
You think they would want to do yoga here?

283
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,210
Come on.
It'd be nice to do it first thing.

284
00:09:04,293 --> 00:09:06,128
- Okay, some stretching.
- To help us wake up.

285
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:08,506
Great. So tomorrow morning,
we can do some yoga.

286
00:09:08,589 --> 00:09:10,258
Yeah, that's exactly what we need.

287
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:11,259
This is great.

288
00:09:11,342 --> 00:09:13,135
So we provide three meals a day.

289
00:09:13,719 --> 00:09:16,013
You barely have time to breathe
before you have to cook again.

290
00:09:16,097 --> 00:09:17,640
Then I guess we should start cooking soon.

291
00:09:17,723 --> 00:09:19,517
- Speaking of dinner…
- What are you thinking?

292
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:22,061
- We were thinking we could do pork katsu.
- How?

293
00:09:22,144 --> 00:09:23,312
- For Pork katsu, we--
- Where's the meat from?

294
00:09:23,396 --> 00:09:24,939
The meat? We're picking it up.

295
00:09:25,022 --> 00:09:26,649
- Ah!
- So we just need to deep-fry it?

296
00:09:26,732 --> 00:09:28,359
- Deep-fry.
- Deep-fry, okay.

297
00:09:28,442 --> 00:09:30,236
But we can't just have pork katsu.

298
00:09:30,319 --> 00:09:32,405
- We can slice up some cabbage.
- We were planning to slice up cabbage.

299
00:09:32,488 --> 00:09:33,489
Did you order it?

300
00:09:33,573 --> 00:09:34,991
- I knew you'd get it.
- That's good.

301
00:09:35,074 --> 00:09:36,659
- Will that be enough? Maybe--
- Pickled radish.

302
00:09:36,742 --> 00:09:38,160
Pickled radish. Good.

303
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:40,162
- We gotta do that. Pineapple too!
- That's a great idea.

304
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:42,123
This is really coming together.

305
00:09:42,206 --> 00:09:44,458
Don't we need
something like doenjang soup?

306
00:09:44,959 --> 00:09:47,128
That's right,
pork katsu can be a little dry.

307
00:09:47,211 --> 00:09:48,754
- We should have soup.
- Is it quick to make?

308
00:09:48,838 --> 00:09:51,007
We just need tofu, spinach,
seaweed and doenjang.

309
00:09:52,008 --> 00:09:54,260
- You guys are seriously next level!
- Anchovies too.

310
00:09:54,343 --> 00:09:57,722
It's nothing special. It's the basics.
If this is impressive to you, I don't--

311
00:09:57,805 --> 00:09:59,390
- You should've seen what we served before.
- Exactly.

312
00:09:59,473 --> 00:10:00,808
How do you invite people without a plan?

313
00:10:00,891 --> 00:10:03,102
You sure you can't stay longer?

314
00:10:03,185 --> 00:10:04,020
Seriously.

315
00:10:05,104 --> 00:10:06,063
- Jae-seok.
- Yes?

316
00:10:06,147 --> 00:10:08,524
- When are we playing the game?
- We should go now.

317
00:10:08,608 --> 00:10:09,984
It's 3:12.

318
00:10:10,067 --> 00:10:11,277
- We should go now.
- Where are we going?

319
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,278
We gather there.

320
00:10:12,361 --> 00:10:14,238
- Down there?
- Mm-hmm.

321
00:10:14,822 --> 00:10:15,865
All right.

322
00:10:15,948 --> 00:10:18,075
We do one activity per day,
and in a moment,

323
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:21,245
we'll be starting the first activity
of your stay with us.

324
00:10:21,329 --> 00:10:25,374
Everyone inside and outside,
please gather in the gymnasium.

325
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:27,209
We'll see you in just a bit.

326
00:10:28,502 --> 00:10:29,337
Thank you.

327
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:30,588
JAE-SEOK'S B&B RULES!

328
00:10:30,671 --> 00:10:31,672
Let's head down.

329
00:10:31,756 --> 00:10:33,299
ONE ACTIVITY PER DAY

330
00:10:33,382 --> 00:10:35,301
It's gonna get hot.

331
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:38,304
- Where did you get that Kancho?
- Oh!

332
00:10:38,804 --> 00:10:41,098
Sorry, it's for Woo-seok.
It has his name on it.

333
00:10:41,182 --> 00:10:42,391
- No way!
- You found it?

334
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:44,060
- I did.
- Whoa! No way!

335
00:10:44,143 --> 00:10:45,728
- You found it?
- Found what?

336
00:10:45,811 --> 00:10:47,146
I've been looking for this!

337
00:10:47,229 --> 00:10:49,231
- Really? You found "Woo-seok"?
- Yeah.

338
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:51,734
BYEON WOO-SEOK

339
00:10:51,817 --> 00:10:54,695
- I wish you'd found Jae-seok.
- Hey, back up.

340
00:10:55,279 --> 00:10:56,322
- No!
- Hey.

341
00:10:57,073 --> 00:10:59,408
- You saved the one with a heart.
- Yeah, that's right.

342
00:11:00,534 --> 00:11:01,827
Why haven't you found mine?

343
00:11:02,828 --> 00:11:04,622
TEAM KWANG-SOO: HA-NA, I-AN
TEAM YE-EUN: HYE-JEONG, MIN-JU

344
00:11:04,705 --> 00:11:06,332
Don't you guys eat Kancho?

345
00:11:06,957 --> 00:11:09,210
- They don't have a Kwang-soo.
- I don't think there's a Kwang-soo.

346
00:11:09,293 --> 00:11:10,836
- They only have common names.
- Why not?

347
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:11,754
Yeah.

348
00:11:11,837 --> 00:11:13,714
I don't know a single other Kwang-soo.

349
00:11:13,798 --> 00:11:14,715
- Yeah, not one.
- No one.

350
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:16,008
Except on <i>I am SOLO</i>.

351
00:11:17,385 --> 00:11:19,011
Honestly, neither have I.

352
00:11:19,095 --> 00:11:20,262
Oh, really?

353
00:11:20,346 --> 00:11:22,139
- One of a kind.
- Right?

354
00:11:22,765 --> 00:11:24,642
- What game are we playing?
- All right.

355
00:11:25,476 --> 00:11:27,603
I told you we'd be doing
one activity per day.

356
00:11:27,687 --> 00:11:29,605
Let's start your first activity right now.

357
00:11:33,442 --> 00:11:35,861
First things first,
let's all go check out the game room,

358
00:11:35,945 --> 00:11:37,905
and we'll find out what we'll be playing.

359
00:11:38,489 --> 00:11:41,033
- Oh, there's a separate game room?
- I guess they must have one

360
00:11:41,117 --> 00:11:42,493
in the back over there.

361
00:11:42,576 --> 00:11:44,704
Oh, looks like we're going inside.

362
00:11:44,787 --> 00:11:46,580
Let's all go check out the game room.

363
00:11:46,664 --> 00:11:48,124
- What? Game room?
- I didn't see that.

364
00:11:48,207 --> 00:11:49,041
- Where is it?
- I guess so.

365
00:11:49,125 --> 00:11:50,209
- Right?
- I'm scared.

366
00:11:50,292 --> 00:11:52,837
- There must be another space behind that.
- Oh, really?

367
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,839
I think there's
something behind that wall.

368
00:11:54,922 --> 00:11:55,798
Oh, really?

369
00:11:56,298 --> 00:11:57,466
Are you surprised?

370
00:11:57,550 --> 00:12:01,262
Whoa!

371
00:12:01,971 --> 00:12:03,848
Wow, no way!

372
00:12:03,931 --> 00:12:06,434
- I didn't see that coming.
- I now present to you all…

373
00:12:06,517 --> 00:12:09,645
the game room!

374
00:12:12,982 --> 00:12:13,816
PROUD

375
00:12:13,899 --> 00:12:15,025
Amazing!

376
00:12:15,109 --> 00:12:15,943
PROUD 2

377
00:12:16,026 --> 00:12:17,570
- I can't believe it.
- This is so cool.

378
00:12:17,653 --> 00:12:19,280
- Come on in.
- This is unbelievable.

379
00:12:19,363 --> 00:12:20,197
I love it!

380
00:12:20,281 --> 00:12:21,323
HIDDEN SPACE
THE GAME ROOM

381
00:12:21,407 --> 00:12:22,491
Whoa!

382
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:24,827
How cute!

383
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:26,912
Is that for the cushion thing?

384
00:12:27,663 --> 00:12:30,583
This must be that game
they used to play with the cushion.

385
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:32,710
- Isn't it cozy?
- This is great.

386
00:12:32,793 --> 00:12:34,253
- So cool.
- Awesome.

387
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:36,756
They have a lot of stuff.

388
00:12:37,465 --> 00:12:39,258
All right. First, get in your teams.

389
00:12:39,341 --> 00:12:41,469
- Yes.
- You see the uniforms over here?

390
00:12:42,052 --> 00:12:43,012
You'll be using them.

391
00:12:43,095 --> 00:12:45,264
- Do we pick colors?
- Yeah, the captains choose.

392
00:12:45,347 --> 00:12:46,390
- All right.
- Now,

393
00:12:46,891 --> 00:12:49,226
Ye-eun's team has fewer people,

394
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:52,354
so Sang-soon and Hyo-ri, why don't you…

395
00:12:52,855 --> 00:12:54,940
- Join her team?
- …join her team, yeah.

396
00:12:55,024 --> 00:12:57,067
Would you like to stay together?

397
00:12:57,151 --> 00:12:58,819
- Oh, we'll stay together.
- I thought so.

398
00:12:58,903 --> 00:13:00,780
Okay great. I've got you both. Yay!

399
00:13:00,863 --> 00:13:02,948
- All right, Ye-eun, uniforms.
- You know I have separation anxiety.

400
00:13:03,032 --> 00:13:04,825
- How about orange?
- Yes, orange.

401
00:13:04,909 --> 00:13:06,994
- The orange ones look really good.
- Orange all the way.

402
00:13:11,999 --> 00:13:14,460
TEAM WOO-SEOK CHOOSES WHITE

403
00:13:14,543 --> 00:13:15,544
- Here.
- Thank you.

404
00:13:15,628 --> 00:13:16,754
Press it down so it doesn't fall off.

405
00:13:16,837 --> 00:13:17,671
TEAM KWANG-SOO CHOOSES BLACK

406
00:13:18,255 --> 00:13:19,256
CAREFULLY PUTTING ON NAME TAGS

407
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:20,466
- Thanks.
- Sure.

408
00:13:20,549 --> 00:13:22,134
- Let's sit here.
- Let's sit.

409
00:13:22,968 --> 00:13:24,595
- I'm ready.
- This is gonna be fun.

410
00:13:24,678 --> 00:13:25,554
I know, right?

411
00:13:25,638 --> 00:13:28,140
- We have to sit in a line.
- In a line.

412
00:13:28,724 --> 00:13:29,558
CHUCKLE

413
00:13:30,184 --> 00:13:33,020
You know, it's quite refreshing to see
our special guests

414
00:13:33,103 --> 00:13:35,648
Sang-soon and Hyo-ri
lined up as team members.

415
00:13:36,232 --> 00:13:37,233
It's new.

416
00:13:37,316 --> 00:13:39,819
A REFRESHING SIGHT

417
00:13:42,863 --> 00:13:46,116
All right, everyone. I told you
we'd be doing one activity per day.

418
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:49,411
First up is the Cushion Quiz.
I used to do this on <i>Dongeodongrak</i>.

419
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:50,329
That's right.

420
00:13:50,412 --> 00:13:52,748
Some of you might know it,
and some of you might not.

421
00:13:53,332 --> 00:13:54,667
- What is it?
- Those don't know,

422
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:56,335
- raise your hand.
- The Cushion Quiz.

423
00:13:56,919 --> 00:13:58,796
THE CUSHION QUIZ IS NEW
TO SOME GUESTS

424
00:13:58,879 --> 00:14:01,131
- Oh, Sang-soon, you should know.
- I don't know. Really.

425
00:14:01,715 --> 00:14:03,509
Come on, <i>hyung</i>. Stop pretending.

426
00:14:03,592 --> 00:14:04,885
- What is it?
- The Cushion Quiz.

427
00:14:04,969 --> 00:14:06,136
- I can't remember.
- The Cushion Quiz?

428
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:08,597
We took note of the requests
in your applications.

429
00:14:08,681 --> 00:14:11,600
We found that the Cushion Quiz
consistently ranked pretty high

430
00:14:11,684 --> 00:14:13,853
on the list of activities
you all wanted to try.

431
00:14:13,936 --> 00:14:15,104
So we figured we'd give it a go.

432
00:14:15,688 --> 00:14:18,482
- The category is general knowledge.
- I'm so nervous.

433
00:14:18,566 --> 00:14:19,483
- I know!
- Yes?

434
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:20,401
Charles Darwin!

435
00:14:20,484 --> 00:14:22,194
- Correct!
- Yeah!

436
00:14:22,278 --> 00:14:23,988
THE FIRST TO RAISE THEIR CUSHION
GETS TO ANSWER

437
00:14:24,071 --> 00:14:26,115
Depending on the results of this quiz,

438
00:14:26,657 --> 00:14:29,451
the team that comes in last
will sleep outside.

439
00:14:29,535 --> 00:14:31,704
Wow, no way.

440
00:14:32,288 --> 00:14:33,539
I think I'd like that.

441
00:14:33,622 --> 00:14:38,627
The team that comes in second will do
the dishes after breakfast tomorrow.

442
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:40,796
And the team that comes in first,
of course,

443
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:44,258
gets to relax until tomorrow morning.
All right?

444
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:47,261
All right, let's see
who will come in last.

445
00:14:47,344 --> 00:14:48,178
But first,

446
00:14:48,262 --> 00:14:50,139
- starting with Team Lee Kwang-soo…
- Yes.

447
00:14:50,222 --> 00:14:53,183
…let's here from you all
your best team cheer.

448
00:14:54,226 --> 00:14:56,020
What?

449
00:14:56,103 --> 00:14:56,937
What?

450
00:14:57,021 --> 00:14:58,105
A SUDDEN REQUEST
FOR A TEAM CHEER

451
00:14:58,188 --> 00:15:00,649
A cheer. Let's hear your team's cheer.

452
00:15:01,358 --> 00:15:02,192
LOL

453
00:15:02,276 --> 00:15:03,277
Guys…

454
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:05,905
Discuss it. Go ahead and discuss it.
Discuss it.

455
00:15:05,988 --> 00:15:08,198
Does anyone have a special move?

456
00:15:08,282 --> 00:15:10,159
- I only know, "Hey, hey, hey!"
- Ah!

457
00:15:10,743 --> 00:15:12,536
You've never done the Cushion Quiz?

458
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,830
- I don't think so.
- Really?

459
00:15:15,372 --> 00:15:16,916
I don't think I was ever on <i>Dongeodongrak</i>.

460
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:18,167
- Really?
- Yeah.

461
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:20,794
- So you must've been on <i>X-Man</i>.
- I was on <i>X-Man</i>,

462
00:15:20,878 --> 00:15:23,839
and I was on the first episode
of <i>Running Man </i>as a guest.

463
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:25,966
BEEN ON COUNTLESS VARIETY SHOWS
BUT NEVER DONE THE CUSHION QUIZ

464
00:15:26,050 --> 00:15:29,303
Listen, you've got to do your cheer
with confidence. I said confidence.

465
00:15:30,304 --> 00:15:31,388
CRACKS UP (?)

466
00:15:31,472 --> 00:15:34,266
Hyo-ri, you're gonna have
to stop staring at me.

467
00:15:34,350 --> 00:15:36,018
You're gonna have to stop staring at me.

468
00:15:37,478 --> 00:15:39,813
Stop giving me that piercing look.

469
00:15:39,897 --> 00:15:41,148
WHEN JAE-SEOK WAS TALKING

470
00:15:41,231 --> 00:15:44,526
Those of you who were born
in the late '90s and the 2000s…

471
00:15:45,986 --> 00:15:47,571
SHE WAS WATCHING HIM INTENTLY

472
00:15:47,655 --> 00:15:50,157
You know, Hyo-Ri and I
used to film things together all the time

473
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:52,743
but now it's weird having her
watch me from the sidelines.

474
00:15:53,744 --> 00:15:56,372
It's like your younger sibling
coming to your workplace and watching you.

475
00:15:56,455 --> 00:15:57,790
It's so uncomfortable.

476
00:15:57,873 --> 00:16:00,000
- I can see you're working hard.
- Right.

477
00:16:00,084 --> 00:16:01,919
All right, then.

478
00:16:02,002 --> 00:16:04,421
- Let's start with Team Kwang-soo.
- Okay.

479
00:16:04,505 --> 00:16:06,090
- Ours is short.
- That's fine.

480
00:16:06,173 --> 00:16:08,467
It's okay even if it's short.

481
00:16:09,051 --> 00:16:10,469
- Should we start?
- Yes, go ahead.

482
00:16:10,552 --> 00:16:11,595
Team Kwang-soo!

