OUT OF NOWHERE,
IT'S "COME ON" TIME

1209
00:41:28,527 --> 00:41:29,737
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

1210
00:41:29,820 --> 00:41:30,654
GIVES UP

1211
00:41:31,280 --> 00:41:32,823
Why does he keep saying "come on"?

1212
00:41:32,907 --> 00:41:34,825
What's wrong with your dad, Chae-won?

1213
00:41:34,909 --> 00:41:37,286
I can't get into it otherwise.
I need a "come on."

1214
00:41:37,369 --> 00:41:40,206
I bet your dad
used to party back in his day.

1215
00:41:40,289 --> 00:41:42,708
I bet he got something good.

1216
00:41:42,791 --> 00:41:44,126
All right, it's pork katsu!

1217
00:41:44,210 --> 00:41:46,086
Pork katsu!

1218
00:41:46,170 --> 00:41:47,880
All right, please take them inside.

1219
00:41:47,963 --> 00:41:49,131
Sure.

1220
00:41:52,009 --> 00:41:52,968
No way.

1221
00:41:53,052 --> 00:41:55,638
- We have to deep-fry it.
- Oh, they're gonna deep-fry it here?

1222
00:41:55,721 --> 00:41:57,306
- Yeah, they do it here.
- Wow.

1223
00:41:57,389 --> 00:42:00,267
- Pretty fancy, huh? Right?
- Yeah.

1224
00:42:00,351 --> 00:42:03,103
When it comes to food, we don't hold back.

1225
00:42:04,104 --> 00:42:05,397
Aren't you here with your brother?

1226
00:42:05,481 --> 00:42:07,358
- Yeah, I am.
- Who's your brother, Nam-jin?

1227
00:42:07,441 --> 00:42:08,776
- Nam-soon.
- Oh, Nam-soon.

1228
00:42:08,859 --> 00:42:09,777
He's over there.

1229
00:42:09,860 --> 00:42:11,570
We're not brother and sister.

1230
00:42:11,654 --> 00:42:12,905
I know that now.

1231
00:42:12,988 --> 00:42:14,615
You guys are brothers, here together.

1232
00:42:14,698 --> 00:42:15,991
NAM-SOON, OCCUPATION: ??
NAM-JIN, OCCUPATION: ??

1233
00:42:16,075 --> 00:42:17,243
Hye-jeong, did you make a video?

1234
00:42:17,326 --> 00:42:19,662
Oh, yeah, we're making
a video together. Join us.

1235
00:42:19,745 --> 00:42:20,746
What kind of video?

1236
00:42:20,829 --> 00:42:22,414
Wow!

1237
00:42:22,498 --> 00:42:23,749
LAUGHING

1238
00:42:24,333 --> 00:42:25,793
IN THE ZONE

1239
00:42:27,211 --> 00:42:28,462
- What are you doing?
- What?

1240
00:42:28,546 --> 00:42:29,630
What's with…

1241
00:42:29,713 --> 00:42:31,715
You're supposed to make up
a dance like this at the end.

1242
00:42:31,799 --> 00:42:33,342
- What's this?
- Free-style at the end,

1243
00:42:33,425 --> 00:42:34,426
- right?
- Hey, Jae-seok.

1244
00:42:34,510 --> 00:42:37,054
- Yeah?
- Can you make a reel with us?

1245
00:42:37,137 --> 00:42:38,013
What you got?

1246
00:42:38,097 --> 00:42:41,433
First, Hyo-ri and I will stand here
and shoot you up.

1247
00:42:41,517 --> 00:42:43,060
- You just jump like this.
- From both sides?

1248
00:42:43,143 --> 00:42:45,229
- Come closer.
- Can you tell me what it's for first?

1249
00:42:45,312 --> 00:42:46,355
- Just do it.
- Yeah.

1250
00:42:46,438 --> 00:42:48,190
- One…
- One, two, three.

1251
00:42:48,732 --> 00:42:49,733
…three.

1252
00:42:51,777 --> 00:42:53,195
- Like this?
- Yes, that was good.

1253
00:42:53,279 --> 00:42:55,155
Do body rolls like this.

1254
00:42:55,239 --> 00:42:56,699
- Like this?
- But face that way.

1255
00:42:56,782 --> 00:42:58,242
- But that way.
- Yeah.

1256
00:42:58,325 --> 00:42:59,660
Don't jump at us!

1257
00:43:00,286 --> 00:43:02,371
- I'm not jumping at you. What?
- Just get closer. Closer.

1258
00:43:03,205 --> 00:43:04,665
NOT SURE WHAT'S GOING ON,
BUT DOING AS TOLD

1259
00:43:04,748 --> 00:43:05,874
Oh, like…

1260
00:43:05,958 --> 00:43:08,752
- <i>You and me…</i>
- <i>You and me walking down the street </i>

1261
00:43:28,772 --> 00:43:30,482
This is actually kind of a workout,

1262
00:43:30,566 --> 00:43:31,650
- right?
- Yeah, it is.

1263
00:43:31,734 --> 00:43:32,735
AFTER A FULL ROUND OF REEL FUN

1264
00:43:34,278 --> 00:43:35,613
- Are you hungry?
- Yeah.

1265
00:43:36,905 --> 00:43:39,074
Wait, what's going on
with these sweet potatoes?

1266
00:43:39,575 --> 00:43:40,534
Are they cooking or not?

1267
00:43:40,618 --> 00:43:41,952
I don't think they are.

1268
00:43:43,829 --> 00:43:44,830
CRUNCHY

1269
00:43:46,332 --> 00:43:47,499
Yup, that's raw.

1270
00:43:49,126 --> 00:43:50,628
- Get the big ones, Kwang-soo.
- Okay.

1271
00:43:50,711 --> 00:43:51,629
PREPPED SINCE 10 A.M.

1272
00:43:53,631 --> 00:43:54,923
This machine isn't working.

1273
00:43:55,007 --> 00:43:56,008
STILL NOT COOKING HOURS LATER

1274
00:43:56,091 --> 00:43:57,301
The temperature?

1275
00:43:57,384 --> 00:43:59,595
- It should be higher, right?
- Maybe that's the problem.

1276
00:43:59,678 --> 00:44:01,221
- This is as high as it goes.
- Right.

1277
00:44:01,847 --> 00:44:03,766
- What is it?
- It's not working.

1278
00:44:04,391 --> 00:44:07,019
WHAT COULD BE THE PROBLEM?

1279
00:44:09,772 --> 00:44:12,232
- Oh, come on! I made a mistake.
- You're supposed to use this.

1280
00:44:13,067 --> 00:44:14,401
There's a space underneath the coals

1281
00:44:14,485 --> 00:44:16,779
where you're supposed
to roast the sweet potatoes.

1282
00:44:18,197 --> 00:44:20,741
This is where you put
the ones that are already cooked.

1283
00:44:20,824 --> 00:44:21,700
Man, of course.

1284
00:44:21,784 --> 00:44:24,370
We've been trying to cook them
for ten hours.

1285
00:44:24,453 --> 00:44:26,121
No wonder it wasn't working.

1286
00:44:26,205 --> 00:44:27,206
(FINALLY IN THE RIGHT PLACE)

1287
00:44:27,289 --> 00:44:28,457
Of course, that's why.

1288
00:44:28,540 --> 00:44:31,210
I just kept thinking,
"Why aren't they cooking?"

1289
00:44:32,086 --> 00:44:33,587
How old did you say you were?

1290
00:44:33,671 --> 00:44:35,089
- We're not supposed to tell yet.
- Ah.

1291
00:44:35,172 --> 00:44:36,590
- But you're around my age.
- That's why I haven't told.

1292
00:44:36,674 --> 00:44:38,592
When I was a high school senior,

1293
00:44:38,676 --> 00:44:39,885
my dream was to marry you,

1294
00:44:40,636 --> 00:44:42,596
I tried to study,
but you kept distracting me like…

1295
00:44:42,680 --> 00:44:43,889
Here, look at me.

1296
00:44:43,972 --> 00:44:45,974
So I kept looking at you
and couldn't concentrate.

1297
00:44:46,058 --> 00:44:48,686
You know, his jokes aren't funny,
but he really tries, huh?

1298
00:44:48,769 --> 00:44:50,104
Is he always like this?

1299
00:44:50,187 --> 00:44:51,980
Yeah, he likes to joke.

1300
00:44:52,648 --> 00:44:55,609
WHO IS THIS DAD WHO'S SO HUNGRY
FOR DANCING AND JOKES?

1301
00:44:56,402 --> 00:44:58,278
CURRENT TIME 5:30 P.M.
(1 HOUR UNTIL DINNER)

1302
00:44:58,362 --> 00:45:00,155
- Are we gonna cook in here?
- Yeah.

1303
00:45:00,239 --> 00:45:01,407
The pork katsu's already here.

1304
00:45:01,490 --> 00:45:02,491
Oh, it's here?

1305
00:45:02,574 --> 00:45:04,993
- Do we have plates though?
- Yeah, we do.

1306
00:45:06,245 --> 00:45:07,871
How much water do we need for soup?

1307
00:45:08,539 --> 00:45:09,540
Whoa!

1308
00:45:09,623 --> 00:45:10,791
Let me get that.

1309
00:45:12,418 --> 00:45:14,545
You're all talk.
You just said you'd get it.

1310
00:45:14,628 --> 00:45:16,922
- You only said it to get it on mic.
- No, that's not--

1311
00:45:17,005 --> 00:45:18,382
You knew nobody can
actually see down there.

1312
00:45:18,465 --> 00:45:20,259
- No, I said I'd get it.
- Your hands weren't moving.

1313
00:45:20,342 --> 00:45:21,260
No, I got it.

1314
00:45:21,343 --> 00:45:23,303
You said you would
but you didn't even move your hands.

1315
00:45:23,387 --> 00:45:24,471
Oh, get out of here.

1316
00:45:28,600 --> 00:45:29,601
More?

1317
00:45:30,144 --> 00:45:32,438
- Just a little more than half. Yeah.
- Mmm.

1318
00:45:32,521 --> 00:45:36,066
- Whoa, you just sounded like…
- I sounded like… like a pro, right?

1319
00:45:36,150 --> 00:45:38,318
Like you owned a gukbap joint
for 40 years.

1320
00:45:39,361 --> 00:45:40,863
I'm boiling the water.

1321
00:45:40,946 --> 00:45:42,781
BOILS WATER FOR DOENJANG SOUP

1322
00:45:43,615 --> 00:45:46,744
AND HEATS UP OIL FOR PORK KATSU

1323
00:45:46,827 --> 00:45:48,495
- Okay, they're back.
- Oh, they're here.

1324
00:45:49,079 --> 00:45:50,664
- Good job, everyone.
- Well done.

1325
00:45:50,748 --> 00:45:51,749
Good work.

1326
00:45:52,499 --> 00:45:54,042
Oh, honey.

1327
00:45:54,126 --> 00:45:56,211
- Channeling Jang-geum?
- Who, me?

1328
00:45:56,295 --> 00:45:57,838
The vibe's already different.

1329
00:45:57,921 --> 00:46:00,841
So I guess we'll be running
everything by you two today.

1330
00:46:02,342 --> 00:46:03,594
HAIR UP

1331
00:46:04,178 --> 00:46:05,220
APRON ON

1332
00:46:05,804 --> 00:46:07,473
HEAD CHEF LEE HYO-RI

1333
00:46:08,056 --> 00:46:10,142
SOUS CHEF LEE SANG-SOON

1334
00:46:10,225 --> 00:46:12,227
How can I help? What should I do?

1335
00:46:12,311 --> 00:46:14,897
It'd be great if you could slice this.
Sit over there.

1336
00:46:14,980 --> 00:46:16,815
- Should I cut the onions?
- Yeah.

1337
00:46:16,899 --> 00:46:18,817
- Ye-eun, we need to slice the tofu.
- Oh, okay.

1338
00:46:18,901 --> 00:46:21,069
- Then you cook the rice, <i>oppa</i>.
- All right, I'll do it.

1339
00:46:22,070 --> 00:46:22,988
(RICE) - (GREEN ONION)
(CABBAGE) - (TOFU)

1340
00:46:23,071 --> 00:46:23,906
TASKS ASSIGNED IN A FLASH

1341
00:46:23,989 --> 00:46:26,241
It's so nice to have
someone take charge of the food.

1342
00:46:26,325 --> 00:46:27,701
It's easier. So much easier.

1343
00:46:27,785 --> 00:46:30,954
Hey, Hyo-ri, it's really great
to have you and Sang-soon.

1344
00:46:31,038 --> 00:46:32,915
Man, I've got nothing to worry about now.

1345
00:46:35,125 --> 00:46:38,045
MEASURING OUT RICE

1346
00:46:40,214 --> 00:46:41,381
Do we need more?

1347
00:46:42,299 --> 00:46:44,176
- We're gonna need way more than that.
- Really?

1348
00:46:44,259 --> 00:46:47,471
That right there is only enough
for six or seven people at most.

1349
00:46:47,971 --> 00:46:49,765
Just two more cups should do it. Yeah.

1350
00:46:50,349 --> 00:46:51,767
- This should do it.
- Yeah.

1351
00:46:52,518 --> 00:46:54,686
- I'll let the rice soak a bit first.
- Okay.

1352
00:46:56,063 --> 00:46:59,483
We don't have enough time
to soak it, so just cook it.

1353
00:47:01,193 --> 00:47:02,903
- Oh, you heard that?
- Yes.

1354
00:47:02,986 --> 00:47:05,155
- Thanks for paying attention.
- Sure.

1355
00:47:05,239 --> 00:47:07,032
I'm always watching you.

1356
00:47:07,825 --> 00:47:10,494
Can I cook this behind you?
It's kinda crowded there.

1357
00:47:10,577 --> 00:47:12,329
- You can do it behind me.
- Yeah, that's okay?

1358
00:47:14,790 --> 00:47:17,334
You know, I think
you're especially nice to Woo-seok.

1359
00:47:19,545 --> 00:47:20,879
<i>Nuna</i>, we have these!

1360
00:47:21,630 --> 00:47:22,798
We have these too.

1361
00:47:22,881 --> 00:47:23,882
Oh, good.

1362
00:47:23,966 --> 00:47:25,634
(DONE)

1363
00:47:25,717 --> 00:47:28,762
Come on, give Kwang-soo
something more than that.

1364
00:47:28,846 --> 00:47:30,430
<i>Nuna</i>, it was really hard to find these.

1365
00:47:30,514 --> 00:47:31,515
Kwang-soo, you're…

1366
00:47:31,598 --> 00:47:33,475
- I wasn't gonna say anything…
- You've been doing a good job.

1367
00:47:33,559 --> 00:47:35,143
You treat the two of them so different.

1368
00:47:35,227 --> 00:47:36,895
- They were hard to find.
- Right, I see.

1369
00:47:36,979 --> 00:47:38,313
- Thank you so much.
- All right.

1370
00:47:38,397 --> 00:47:39,731
PLEASED

1371
00:47:40,315 --> 00:47:42,359
MEANWHILE, WOO-SEOK IS…?

1372
00:47:43,151 --> 00:47:45,279
FOCUSING ON SLICING CABBAGE

1373
00:47:47,865 --> 00:47:50,284
- You're better than I expected.
- You're good at that, <i>oppa</i>.

1374
00:47:50,367 --> 00:47:52,494
I guess eggs just weren't my thing.

1375
00:47:53,287 --> 00:47:54,288
This feels good.

1376
00:47:54,371 --> 00:47:55,247
EGG GUY FINDS A NEW TALENT

1377
00:47:55,330 --> 00:47:57,249
I think I'm good at chopping onions.

1378
00:47:58,041 --> 00:47:59,501
I think I'm good at slicing cabbage.

1379
00:47:59,585 --> 00:48:02,546
Look how even it is.
A lot of people end up cutting themselves.

1380
00:48:03,797 --> 00:48:05,007
SMOOTH SAILING AT EVERY STATION

1381
00:48:05,591 --> 00:48:06,592
This big?

1382
00:48:07,092 --> 00:48:08,385
Hey, you know what?

1383
00:48:08,886 --> 00:48:13,223
For the first time, this kitchen
actually feels peaceful and organized.

1384
00:48:13,307 --> 00:48:14,474
- Totally.
- Honestly,

1385
00:48:14,558 --> 00:48:15,726
my confidence just went up.

1386
00:48:15,809 --> 00:48:18,437
I actually feel like I'm good
at cooking right now.

1387
00:48:18,520 --> 00:48:20,647
- We're doing it!
- I know, right?

1388
00:48:20,731 --> 00:48:23,692
When are they gonna share
their jobs and personal life?

1389
00:48:23,775 --> 00:48:26,069
Tomorrow. Their jobs and ages.

1390
00:48:26,153 --> 00:48:26,987
Tomorrow?

1391
00:48:27,070 --> 00:48:28,322
That's right.

1392
00:48:28,906 --> 00:48:30,699
YE-EUN FINISHES CUTTING TOFU
FOR THE DOENJANG SOUP

1393
00:48:30,782 --> 00:48:31,658
Done.

1394
00:48:32,826 --> 00:48:34,202
I'll cut the radish.

1395
00:48:34,286 --> 00:48:35,746
MOVING RIGHT ON
TO CUTTING PICKLED RADISH

1396
00:48:35,829 --> 00:48:38,206
But maybe don't do it here because it…

1397
00:48:38,290 --> 00:48:40,208
- it might get on the cabbage.
- Oh, I see.

1398
00:48:40,292 --> 00:48:41,418
Then what do I do?

1399
00:48:41,501 --> 00:48:43,921
- Just imagine there's a line here.
- Okay.

1400
00:48:44,004 --> 00:48:45,380
I'll stay on this side.

1401
00:48:45,881 --> 00:48:48,634
- Is this about the right length?
- Yeah, that looks good. Mmm.

1402
00:48:49,301 --> 00:48:50,469
I don't know.

1403
00:48:52,346 --> 00:48:53,680
CHOPPING IN BIG CHUNKS

1404
00:48:54,264 --> 00:48:56,475
- Wait, the radish…
- What about it?

1405
00:48:56,558 --> 00:48:58,518
You keep inching over this way.

1406
00:48:58,602 --> 00:49:00,228
Oh, really?

1407
00:49:00,312 --> 00:49:01,772
(PROTECTING HIS CABBAGE)

1408
00:49:05,150 --> 00:49:07,194
Try cutting a bit more neatly.

1409
00:49:07,277 --> 00:49:10,656
Instead of cutting it all at once,
how about doing five pieces at a time?

1410
00:49:10,739 --> 00:49:13,408
The cabbage is getting pickle juice
all over it right now.

1411
00:49:13,492 --> 00:49:14,326
It's all covered.

1412
00:49:14,409 --> 00:49:15,869
- Ye-eun.
- Oh. Yes?

1413
00:49:15,953 --> 00:49:17,287
DO BETTER, WILL YOU?

1414
00:49:17,371 --> 00:49:19,456
Hyo-ri didn't use to let that slide.

1415
00:49:19,539 --> 00:49:20,707
"Hey, Ye-eun!"

1416
00:49:20,791 --> 00:49:21,833
He's right, yeah.

1417
00:49:22,501 --> 00:49:24,127
Just be glad you met me now.

1418
00:49:24,211 --> 00:49:25,879
Back in the day, she wasn't so patient.

1419
00:49:27,047 --> 00:49:29,841
THE SOUS CHEF'S COOKING QUIETLY
BY HIMSELF

1420
00:49:31,551 --> 00:49:33,136
CAREFUL HEAT CONTROL

1421
00:49:34,304 --> 00:49:35,514
PRECISE TEMPERATURE CHECK

1422
00:49:53,073 --> 00:49:55,117
The katsu look amazing.

1423
00:49:55,200 --> 00:49:56,368
Whoa!

1424
00:49:57,119 --> 00:49:58,161
Look at the katsu.

1425
00:49:58,245 --> 00:50:00,539
- Wait, what? You already fried them?
- Look at them, <i>hyung</i>.

1426
00:50:00,622 --> 00:50:01,832
They look store-bought.

1427
00:50:01,915 --> 00:50:03,917
- That's a nice color.
- It's just about there.

1428
00:50:04,001 --> 00:50:05,252
Whoa!

1429
00:50:06,086 --> 00:50:08,588
I think we should give them
one more quick deep-fry.

1430
00:50:09,840 --> 00:50:13,093
DOUBLE-FRYING
FOR EXTRA CRISPINESS

1431
00:50:13,176 --> 00:50:14,511
<i>Hyung</i>, try one.

1432
00:50:14,594 --> 00:50:16,346
- All right.
- See if they're cooked well.

1433
00:50:17,472 --> 00:50:20,475
HOW DOES SANG-SOON'S
PORK CUTLET TASTE?

1434
00:50:21,101 --> 00:50:22,019
Wow.

1435
00:50:22,102 --> 00:50:23,103
- Mmm!
- Whoa!

1436
00:50:23,937 --> 00:50:25,105
- Is it good?
- Very good.

1437
00:50:25,188 --> 00:50:26,273
Okay.

1438
00:50:26,356 --> 00:50:28,650
- It's good? Is it cooked through?
- It's so good. Yeah.

1439
00:50:28,734 --> 00:50:30,610
- Really, really good.
- Well done.

1440
00:50:30,694 --> 00:50:32,529
DEEP-FRYING FISH KATSU
FOR HYO-RI

1441
00:50:32,612 --> 00:50:34,614
Put them here and I'll cut 'em.

1442
00:50:34,698 --> 00:50:35,657
Nice cutting.

1443
00:50:36,241 --> 00:50:37,576
It's all sliced.

1444
00:50:37,659 --> 00:50:39,786
The pork katsu looks insane right now.

1445
00:50:39,870 --> 00:50:41,079
PORK CUTLET SET COMPLETE

1446
00:50:41,163 --> 00:50:42,956
TO THE DOENJANG BROTH
+GREEN ONIONS

1447
00:50:43,540 --> 00:50:45,125
+TOFU

1448
00:50:45,792 --> 00:50:48,211
WITH SPINACH PREPPED BY HYO-RI

1449
00:50:48,837 --> 00:50:50,088
Okay, the soup's done.

1450
00:50:50,172 --> 00:50:52,007
DOENJANG SOUP COMPLETE

1451
00:50:52,090 --> 00:50:53,425
I'm actually excited for our meal.

1452
00:50:53,508 --> 00:50:54,384
Yeah, me too.

1453
00:50:54,468 --> 00:50:55,719
Feels like a hotel.

1454
00:50:56,303 --> 00:50:58,930
If I could cook like you guys,
this would actually be fun.

1455
00:50:59,014 --> 00:51:01,850
I wish the first group of
guests could've gotten a meal like this.

1456
00:51:01,933 --> 00:51:02,976
Ah, man.

1457
00:51:03,477 --> 00:51:06,229
- What time is it, <i>oppa</i>?
- It's about 6:20.

1458
00:51:06,313 --> 00:51:09,274
The timing's perfect.
We're all set, right?

1459
00:51:09,357 --> 00:51:11,151
- We should eat while it's hot.
- You think so?

1460
00:51:11,234 --> 00:51:12,569
- I'll call them over then.
- Yeah.

1461
00:51:13,153 --> 00:51:14,488
All right, you must be hungry.

1462
00:51:15,322 --> 00:51:16,656
- It's dinner time!
- Nice!

1463
00:51:16,740 --> 00:51:17,574
RELAXED, CONFIDENT

1464
00:51:17,657 --> 00:51:18,825
- Okay!
- Oh, okay.

1465
00:51:18,909 --> 00:51:20,285
- Nice.
- Let's go.

1466
00:51:20,368 --> 00:51:22,287
This place
really has a nice vibe at night.

1467
00:51:22,370 --> 00:51:23,413
It's all the lights.

1468
00:51:23,497 --> 00:51:24,581
I'm hungry. Yeah.

1469
00:51:24,664 --> 00:51:26,583
- Smells good in here.
- Welcome.

1470
00:51:26,666 --> 00:51:28,126
We've got pork katsu.

1471
00:51:28,210 --> 00:51:30,420
- This is doenjang soup.
- Yeah.

1472
00:51:30,504 --> 00:51:32,923
The ones at the end are fish katsu,

1473
00:51:33,006 --> 00:51:35,675
so if you don't eat pork,
you can have those.

1474
00:51:35,759 --> 00:51:38,261
If you like fish, feel free to have it.

1475
00:51:38,345 --> 00:51:41,473
I'm just gonna put
some fish katsu aside for Hyo-ri.

1476
00:51:44,017 --> 00:51:45,185
I'll put your soup here.

1477
00:51:45,268 --> 00:51:46,269
Thank you.

1478
00:51:52,651 --> 00:51:54,986
This is basically a hotel.

1479
00:51:55,070 --> 00:51:56,696
Looks a bit better than lunch, right?

1480
00:51:56,780 --> 00:51:58,615
- Yeah, it looks way better.
- Totally.

1481
00:51:59,658 --> 00:52:00,951
You don't want this?

1482
00:52:01,535 --> 00:52:02,953
- No.
- No veggies for her.

1483
00:52:03,036 --> 00:52:04,746
Oh. We worked really hard on it.

1484
00:52:04,830 --> 00:52:06,414
- Oh, then I'll have some.
- Thanks.

1485
00:52:06,498 --> 00:52:07,415
- This much?
- Yeah.

1486
00:52:07,999 --> 00:52:09,709
Great. Wow.

1487
00:52:09,793 --> 00:52:10,710
Can I take over?

1488
00:52:10,794 --> 00:52:13,130
Sure, but this is actually
pretty hard to scoop.

1489
00:52:13,839 --> 00:52:16,967
- Oh, no. Let's just share one.
- Got it. He's ladling it out for us too.

1490
00:52:17,050 --> 00:52:18,802
- I know, I can see.
- Are there enough plates?

1491
00:52:18,885 --> 00:52:20,345
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

1492
00:52:20,428 --> 00:52:21,263
You're welcome.

1493
00:52:22,556 --> 00:52:23,974
I'm taking this home.

1494
00:52:25,100 --> 00:52:26,685
Do you want the ladle too?

1495
00:52:26,768 --> 00:52:28,019
LIMITED EDITION WOO-SEOK MERCH

1496
00:52:28,103 --> 00:52:29,563
Do you like spinach and tofu?

1497
00:52:29,646 --> 00:52:30,689
- Oh, yeah.
- I like them.

1498
00:52:30,772 --> 00:52:33,316
- Okay, enjoy.
- I'll eat anything you give me.

1499
00:52:33,400 --> 00:52:35,777
You're so silly.

1500
00:52:35,861 --> 00:52:37,112
All right, enjoy, everyone.

1501
00:52:37,195 --> 00:52:39,156
- Thank you for the food.
- Enjoy!

1502
00:52:40,365 --> 00:52:41,741
Oh, man!

1503
00:52:43,660 --> 00:52:44,661
The pork is good.

1504
00:52:45,412 --> 00:52:46,621
This is good.

1505
00:52:47,247 --> 00:52:48,373
Mmm. Oh.

1506
00:52:48,456 --> 00:52:50,876
- It's good.
- Yeah, it's really good.

1507
00:52:52,127 --> 00:52:52,961
I don't know.

1508
00:52:53,044 --> 00:52:55,881
- Maybe I should take some medicine first?
- Huh? All right.

1509
00:52:55,964 --> 00:52:57,132
- Want me to go with you?
- Why? What's…

1510
00:52:57,215 --> 00:52:58,300
Her stomach's a little upset.

1511
00:52:58,383 --> 00:53:00,385
Oh, really? You want something for it?

1512
00:53:00,468 --> 00:53:01,469
<i>Hyung</i>, would you take over?

1513
00:53:01,553 --> 00:53:02,846
- I got it, it's okay.
- Thanks.

1514
00:53:04,139 --> 00:53:05,390
- If you wait inside…
- Oh, okay.

1515
00:53:05,473 --> 00:53:07,058
…I'll go check to see
if we have some antacids.

1516
00:53:07,142 --> 00:53:08,143
FIRST SICK GUEST AT THE B&B

1517
00:53:08,935 --> 00:53:10,979
Does it feel like you ate something
and it's not sitting right?

1518
00:53:11,062 --> 00:53:13,315
No, I just have this pain in my stomach.

1519
00:53:17,652 --> 00:53:19,779
BRINGS HER SOME WARM WATER

1520
00:53:19,863 --> 00:53:21,823
- Here's some water.
- Oh, okay.

1521
00:53:22,782 --> 00:53:23,617
Thank you.

1522
00:53:23,700 --> 00:53:24,701
Here it is.

1523
00:53:26,369 --> 00:53:28,580
We've got Tylenol
and something for indigestion.

1524
00:53:29,247 --> 00:53:30,540
- I'll try these.
- Mmm.

1525
00:53:31,374 --> 00:53:33,877
You don't usually take
anything specific, right?

1526
00:53:33,960 --> 00:53:35,587
- That's right.
- Hmm.

1527
00:53:35,670 --> 00:53:36,922
Thank you.

1528
00:53:37,631 --> 00:53:38,965
One pill should do it.

1529
00:53:40,258 --> 00:53:42,802
- If it gets worse, just let me know…
- Sure.

1530
00:53:43,303 --> 00:53:45,180
- …and I'll do whatever I can.
- Oh, okay. Thanks.

1531
00:53:46,056 --> 00:53:47,098
I'm here to help.

1532
00:53:47,724 --> 00:53:48,808
Just ask.

1533
00:53:49,601 --> 00:53:51,061
- Thank you.
- My pleasure.

1534
00:53:51,144 --> 00:53:51,978
CALMLY COMPLETES FIRST AID

1535
00:53:52,062 --> 00:53:53,521
It's our turn now.

1536
00:53:54,105 --> 00:53:55,607
- Hey, Woo-seok, come eat.
- All right.

1537
00:53:55,690 --> 00:53:56,524
This is good.

1538
00:53:56,608 --> 00:53:59,277
- The amount of rice is just perfect.
- Yeah?

1539
00:53:59,361 --> 00:54:02,155
If you hadn't added more,
it wouldn't have been enough, right?

1540
00:54:02,239 --> 00:54:03,531
You were right on the money.

1541
00:54:03,615 --> 00:54:05,325
- It's just right.
- Wow, that's incredible.

1542
00:54:05,408 --> 00:54:06,409
Yes, it is.

1543
00:54:07,744 --> 00:54:09,079
A BITE OF FISH CUTLET

1544
00:54:09,704 --> 00:54:10,705
Mmm.

1545
00:54:10,789 --> 00:54:12,040
- The fish.
- Wow.

1546
00:54:12,123 --> 00:54:13,250
It's so good.

1547
00:54:13,333 --> 00:54:15,085
Ah, the soup is great.

1548
00:54:15,168 --> 00:54:16,753
Wow, it's really good.

1549
00:54:17,462 --> 00:54:18,838
So, pros just don't miss.

1550
00:54:19,798 --> 00:54:22,259
But I think this is my first time
cooking this much food.

1551
00:54:22,342 --> 00:54:23,927
EVEN 1ST-GEN B&B HOSTS
NEVER COOKED THIS MUCH

1552
00:54:24,010 --> 00:54:26,805
Back on <i>Family Outing</i>,
when we made doenjang soup,

1553
00:54:26,888 --> 00:54:30,016
it was supposed to be six servings,
but he'd toss in, like, three anchovies.

1554
00:54:31,142 --> 00:54:32,686
I'd never made it before.

1555
00:54:32,769 --> 00:54:35,188
Still, you should've known
better than that.

1556
00:54:36,481 --> 00:54:37,649
Bryan, how's the food?

1557
00:54:37,732 --> 00:54:39,401
- It's delicious. Yeah.
- Is it okay?

1558
00:54:39,484 --> 00:54:40,610
Get enough, Chae-won?

1559
00:54:40,694 --> 00:54:42,362
- Yeah, I had a lot.
- Oh, yeah?

1560
00:54:45,240 --> 00:54:46,825
SEUNG-JUN GETS
A PORK CUTLET REFILL

1561
00:54:47,575 --> 00:54:49,077
You're really digging in.

1562
00:54:49,160 --> 00:54:51,413
I only got three hours
of sleep last night,

1563
00:54:51,496 --> 00:54:54,082
so I figured I should at least eat
a lot to get some energy back.

1564
00:54:54,165 --> 00:54:55,333
Why so little sleep?

1565
00:54:55,417 --> 00:54:56,459
Too excited?

1566
00:54:57,377 --> 00:54:58,420
Oh, um…

1567
00:54:58,503 --> 00:54:59,796
Do you get off work at two?

1568
00:55:00,297 --> 00:55:02,590
- I was on the phone.
- With who? Your girlfriend?

1569
00:55:02,674 --> 00:55:05,885
- Hey, now…
- She's grilling him. So intense!

1570
00:55:05,969 --> 00:55:07,554
- No questions.
- So scary!

1571
00:55:07,637 --> 00:55:09,639
You can't get into that much detail here.

1572
00:55:09,723 --> 00:55:10,557
But you're curious.

1573
00:55:10,640 --> 00:55:12,392
Don't you wanna know who he called?

1574
00:55:14,728 --> 00:55:16,688
I get the sense you're a musician.

1575
00:55:16,771 --> 00:55:19,190
- I'm nowhere near being a musician.
- Oh, okay.

1576
00:55:19,274 --> 00:55:21,026
Well, I was just guessing.

1577
00:55:21,109 --> 00:55:22,652
I had a feeling I was way off.

1578
00:55:24,571 --> 00:55:26,614
- May I dip it in your sauce?
- Yeah.

1579
00:55:27,240 --> 00:55:28,950
STEALING HIS SAUCE

1580
00:55:29,034 --> 00:55:31,536
Sang-soon, I heard you played
metal music for a bit.

1581
00:55:31,619 --> 00:55:33,455
- Yeah, I did, when I was younger.
- Oh, yeah?

1582
00:55:33,538 --> 00:55:36,458
Is there a reason you didn't stick
with metal and moved on to another genre?

1583
00:55:36,541 --> 00:55:37,792
- He must be a musician.
- Yeah.

1584
00:55:37,876 --> 00:55:39,753
I just like music.
I listen to pretty much everything.

1585
00:55:39,836 --> 00:55:41,212
WHO IS SEUNG-JUN,
THE ONE HYO-RI'S CURIOUS ABOUT?

1586
00:55:41,796 --> 00:55:43,465
Are we doing
another activity after dinner?

1587
00:55:43,548 --> 00:55:45,216
- Fire gazing.
- Oh, yeah?

1588
00:55:45,842 --> 00:55:47,010
Hey, Sang-soon.

1589
00:55:47,093 --> 00:55:49,637
When we have the fire later,
why don't you pluck out a tune for us?

1590
00:55:49,721 --> 00:55:50,889
Well…

1591
00:55:50,972 --> 00:55:52,140
- Like a chicken?
- What?

1592
00:55:52,223 --> 00:55:53,808
You said "pluck," didn't you?

1593
00:55:54,976 --> 00:55:56,144
This is fish.

1594
00:55:56,227 --> 00:55:57,354
Oh, yeah, thanks.

1595
00:55:58,480 --> 00:55:59,856
Good for you, Min-ju.

1596
00:56:00,732 --> 00:56:02,901
Oh!

1597
00:56:03,860 --> 00:56:05,612
- Enjoy your meal.
- Hope you enjoy.

1598
00:56:05,695 --> 00:56:07,447
- Dig in, everyone.
- Enjoy your meal.

1599
00:56:09,199 --> 00:56:10,658
QUICKLY CHECKING HOW SHE LOOKS

1600
00:56:10,742 --> 00:56:13,203
We've got plenty of katsu,
so grab more if you'd like.

1601
00:56:13,286 --> 00:56:14,204
Okay.

1602
00:56:15,455 --> 00:56:16,456
DIZZY

1603
00:56:17,791 --> 00:56:19,292
She's totally lost it.

1604
00:56:19,376 --> 00:56:22,462
You're acting like a little girl
with her first crush.

1605
00:56:23,671 --> 00:56:26,132
- She found her crush.
- You're blushing.

1606
00:56:29,010 --> 00:56:30,845
So, during the off-season,

1607
00:56:30,929 --> 00:56:33,848
do you take a break
or do you keep training?

1608
00:56:33,932 --> 00:56:37,519
Personally, I take about ten days off,
then get back to training.

1609
00:56:37,602 --> 00:56:39,896
- Yeah, something like that.
- Wow.

1610
00:56:39,979 --> 00:56:42,232
But honestly, even when I'm on a break,

1611
00:56:42,315 --> 00:56:44,150
I still go to the gym and work out.

1612
00:56:44,234 --> 00:56:45,652
- That's your break?
- Yeah.

1613
00:56:45,735 --> 00:56:46,986
That's amazing.

1614
00:56:49,948 --> 00:56:52,784
Whoa. Whoa!

1615
00:56:53,910 --> 00:56:57,664
What's wrong with her?
Your ears are all red.

1616
00:56:58,748 --> 00:57:00,333
SUSPICIOUS BEHAVIOR DETECTED

1617
00:57:00,417 --> 00:57:03,169
- Hey, hold on.
- Yeah?

1618
00:57:03,253 --> 00:57:04,254
Yeah?

1619
00:57:04,337 --> 00:57:05,964
Just… No, wait.

1620
00:57:06,047 --> 00:57:08,174
You're looking at Woo-seok like…

1621
00:57:08,258 --> 00:57:10,760
Hye-jeong, what's going on with you guys?

1622
00:57:10,844 --> 00:57:12,887
You were staring at him!

1623
00:57:12,971 --> 00:57:14,139
I mean--

1624
00:57:14,222 --> 00:57:16,057
- This is Jae-seok's B&B.
- Oh, right.

1625
00:57:16,141 --> 00:57:17,183
Time to snap out of it!

1626
00:57:17,267 --> 00:57:19,561
- Yes, Mr. Host.
- I'm sorry, this is <i>Jae-seok's B&B Rules!</i>,

1627
00:57:19,644 --> 00:57:20,687
not Woo-seok's.

1628
00:57:20,770 --> 00:57:21,938
All right?

1629
00:57:23,940 --> 00:57:26,317
<i>Oppa</i>, look. They're satisfied today.

1630
00:57:26,401 --> 00:57:27,360
ALL SATISFIED

1631
00:57:28,069 --> 00:57:31,948
"SATISFACTORY"
WITHOUT A SECOND THOUGHT

1632
00:57:32,031 --> 00:57:34,826
This deserves two of these,
seriously. It deserves two.

1633
00:57:36,536 --> 00:57:38,872
I'm glad. Really glad.

1634
00:57:39,747 --> 00:57:41,082
I'll wash. You guys rinse.

1635
00:57:41,624 --> 00:57:43,918
- You can put some of them in here.
- Can we use that?

1636
00:57:44,002 --> 00:57:45,545
- The scrubber?
- Yeah, I'll use this.

1637
00:57:45,628 --> 00:57:46,671
Hello.

1638
00:57:48,089 --> 00:57:49,174
Hey, rocker.

1639
00:57:49,257 --> 00:57:50,717
I think everyone knows.

1640
00:57:50,800 --> 00:57:51,676
Knows what?

1641
00:57:51,759 --> 00:57:52,927
You're a rocker, right?

1642
00:57:53,011 --> 00:57:54,471
I'm not that good,

1643
00:57:54,554 --> 00:57:56,264
- but I just sing with confidence.
- Are you the lead singer?

1644
00:57:56,347 --> 00:57:57,432
- Yeah.
- Oh.

1645
00:57:57,515 --> 00:57:59,642
I actually major in computer engineering.

1646
00:58:00,226 --> 00:58:03,438
What do you think about AI
replacing everything these days?

1647
00:58:03,521 --> 00:58:04,772
I do think it's possible.

1648
00:58:04,856 --> 00:58:06,191
You think that'll happen soon?

1649
00:58:06,274 --> 00:58:08,318
What if AI ends up controlling humans?

1650
00:58:08,943 --> 00:58:11,321
Are you interested in AI? 'Cause you--

1651
00:58:11,404 --> 00:58:14,032
Well, it's just that these days,
when composers send me songs,

1652
00:58:14,115 --> 00:58:15,533
- like, demos…
- Yeah. Oh, I see.

1653
00:58:15,617 --> 00:58:17,076
…they send them using my voice.

1654
00:58:17,160 --> 00:58:19,412
- So it's already being used like that?
- Mmm.

1655
00:58:19,496 --> 00:58:21,039
I think you get more depth
from a real voice.

1656
00:58:21,122 --> 00:58:21,956
Mmm.

1657
00:58:22,040 --> 00:58:23,750
That instant emotional pull?

1658
00:58:23,833 --> 00:58:26,794
It still feels like AI
can't quite do that yet.

1659
00:58:26,878 --> 00:58:28,213
<i>Hyung</i>,
should we get the firewood?

1660
00:58:28,296 --> 00:58:29,506
Yeah, let's get the wood.

1661
00:58:29,589 --> 00:58:31,883
Dad actually runs a camp ground.

1662
00:58:32,383 --> 00:58:34,469
- He runs one. Yeah.
- Wow, really?

1663
00:58:34,552 --> 00:58:36,763
- He's great at fires.
- Wow, really?

1664
00:58:36,846 --> 00:58:38,306
- Oh, really?
- Can you come with us?

1665
00:58:38,389 --> 00:58:40,391
- Jae-seok!
- What?

1666
00:58:40,475 --> 00:58:41,434
Why?

1667
00:58:41,518 --> 00:58:45,021
- <i>Hyung</i>! Their dad runs a camp ground.
- Oh, really?

1668
00:58:45,104 --> 00:58:46,272
SMILING FROM EAR TO EAR

1669
00:58:46,356 --> 00:58:48,358
- Is that so?
- We were helping him out just last week.

1670
00:58:48,441 --> 00:58:49,943
Let's go then. Come on, come on.

1671
00:58:50,026 --> 00:58:51,778
We were there handing out
roasted sweet potatoes.

1672
00:58:51,861 --> 00:58:52,862
That sounds great.

1673
00:58:52,946 --> 00:58:54,489
Is this the firewood here?

1674
00:58:54,572 --> 00:58:56,032
- Yeah, it is.
- That's right.

1675
00:58:56,115 --> 00:58:57,700
6,000 won, please.

1676
00:58:57,784 --> 00:58:58,826
6,000 won?

1677
00:58:58,910 --> 00:59:01,371
- Sure, let's do it together.
- Wanna give us a hand?

1678
00:59:01,454 --> 00:59:03,957
- You wanna pass it to me?
- I'll take it from here.

1679
00:59:05,041 --> 00:59:06,167
You know how this works.

1680
00:59:06,251 --> 00:59:07,252
LOADING UP ON FIREWOOD

1681
00:59:07,335 --> 00:59:09,212
All right. Okay.

1682
00:59:09,796 --> 00:59:11,714
Over there, to the middle of the field.

1683
00:59:11,798 --> 00:59:13,383
I bet you know how to stack 'em too.

1684
00:59:13,466 --> 00:59:14,509
Yeah.

1685
00:59:14,592 --> 00:59:16,010
Perfect timing.

1686
00:59:16,553 --> 00:59:18,012
- Right?
- Clockwork.

1687
00:59:18,096 --> 00:59:19,764
- So, for fire gazing…
- These are better?

1688
00:59:19,847 --> 00:59:21,766
- Yeah, dry firewood is better.
- That's right.

1689
00:59:21,849 --> 00:59:23,560
Make a hashtag shape.

1690
00:59:24,227 --> 00:59:25,770
I'm so glad you know what you're doing.

1691
00:59:27,355 --> 00:59:29,315
SETTING UP CHAIRS
AROUND THE FIRE

1692
00:59:32,610 --> 00:59:33,987
AND STARTING THE FIRE LIKE A PRO

1693
00:59:34,070 --> 00:59:35,613
Oh, nice, it's catching.

1694
00:59:35,697 --> 00:59:38,199
All right, would all our guests

1695
00:59:38,283 --> 00:59:41,369
who are loving their time
at Jae-seok's B&B,

1696
00:59:41,452 --> 00:59:43,454
- come to the fire gazing?
- Okay.

1697
00:59:43,538 --> 00:59:45,206
- I should go bundle up.
- We've got a bonfire

1698
00:59:45,290 --> 00:59:46,291
outside to keep things warm.

1699
00:59:46,374 --> 00:59:48,418
Come on out, gather around,

1700
00:59:48,501 --> 00:59:50,628
and warm yourselves up by the fire.

1701
00:59:50,712 --> 00:59:51,963
This is what I'm talking about.

1702
00:59:52,046 --> 00:59:52,922
Come on out.

1703
00:59:53,006 --> 00:59:53,923
THEY GATHER BY THE FIRE

1704
00:59:54,007 --> 00:59:55,258
The fire's going strong.

1705
00:59:55,758 --> 00:59:57,677
- It's big, right?
- Yeah.

1706
00:59:57,760 --> 00:59:59,721
- This is it.
- <i>Oppa</i>, come sit.

1707
01:00:00,305 --> 01:00:02,307
THEY ZONE OUT BY THE FIRE
TOGETHER ON THEIR FIRST NIGHT

1708
01:00:02,390 --> 01:00:04,684
By the way, I wonder where Woo-seok is.

1709
01:00:04,767 --> 01:00:05,768
I wonder where Woo-seok is.

1710
01:00:05,852 --> 01:00:07,687
LOOKING AROUND FOR WOO-SEOK
WHO HASN'T SHOWN UP

1711
01:00:09,564 --> 01:00:11,357
Woo-seok isn't coming.

1712
01:00:11,441 --> 01:00:13,234
- What?
- Really?

1713
01:00:13,318 --> 01:00:14,777
- Yeah, he's not coming.
- Why?

1714
01:00:14,861 --> 01:00:16,154
I told him to get some rest inside.

1715
01:00:16,237 --> 01:00:17,238
- Oh.
- Really?

1716
01:00:17,322 --> 01:00:18,323
I'm suddenly tired.

1717
01:00:18,406 --> 01:00:21,492
JUST THEN, A TALL GUY SHOWS UP

1718
01:00:23,995 --> 01:00:26,164
KWANG-SOO INSTEAD OF WOO-SEOK

1719
01:00:28,333 --> 01:00:29,917
Why are there papers on your coat?

1720
01:00:31,878 --> 01:00:34,088
They're not papers.
It's part of the design.

1721
01:00:34,172 --> 01:00:35,173
- Is it?
- Yeah.

1722
01:00:35,256 --> 01:00:36,507
Looks like you got into a fight.

1723
01:00:36,591 --> 01:00:39,010
No, it's the design.
It's the coat's design.

1724
01:00:39,093 --> 01:00:41,262
He's trying to go head-to-head
with Woo-seok.

1725
01:00:41,346 --> 01:00:42,680
What do you mean, head-to-head?

1726
01:00:43,306 --> 01:00:45,058
It's a real competition now.

1727
01:00:45,642 --> 01:00:47,518
HIS RIVAL SHOWS UP

1728
01:00:49,228 --> 01:00:51,314
A WAVE THAT MAKES
YOUR HEART RACE

1729
01:00:51,397 --> 01:00:52,857
You're here.

1730
01:00:54,609 --> 01:00:57,403
- Your eyes will sting over there.
- The smoke. Sit over here.

1731
01:00:57,487 --> 01:00:58,529
Come sit here.

1732
01:00:58,613 --> 01:01:00,657
- Oh, he's sitting there.
- He went the other way.

1733
01:01:00,740 --> 01:01:02,659
<i>Hyung</i>, can't you see I'm crying over here?

1734
01:01:03,660 --> 01:01:05,912
What does it matter
if you're crying, Kwang-soo?

1735
01:01:05,995 --> 01:01:08,331
- Kwang-soo.
- Go on, cry your eyes out.

1736
01:01:08,414 --> 01:01:09,332
MOVES HIS SEAT ON HIS OWN

1737
01:01:10,166 --> 01:01:12,752
FIRE GAZING TIME

1738
01:01:13,711 --> 01:01:15,546
It's nice to stare into the fire.

1739
01:01:17,173 --> 01:01:18,508
I haven't done this in forever.

1740
01:01:18,591 --> 01:01:20,677
- It's warm.
- It is, isn't it?

1741
01:01:20,760 --> 01:01:22,178
It's nice and toasty.

1742
01:01:23,304 --> 01:01:25,556
Ah, it's really warm over here.

1743
01:01:28,309 --> 01:01:30,561
- Wow, look at the leaves falling.
- Wow, that's beautiful.

1744
01:01:33,022 --> 01:01:35,400
- Wow, look at that.
- Whoa.

1745
01:01:35,483 --> 01:01:37,819
- Wow, they're really coming down.
- Oh, my.

1746
01:01:37,902 --> 01:01:40,154
- Autumn's really settling in.
- It really is.

1747
01:01:40,238 --> 01:01:41,239
AUTUMN DEEPENS

1748
01:01:41,322 --> 01:01:42,323
Yeah.

1749
01:01:42,824 --> 01:01:43,825
AND THE NIGHT DEEPENS TOO

1750
01:01:43,908 --> 01:01:45,243
Wow, this is romantic.

1751
01:01:45,326 --> 01:01:46,786
This is the best campfire ever.

1752
01:01:46,869 --> 01:01:48,996
GATHERED UNDER THE AUTUMN
NIGHT SKY, GAZING INTO THE FIRE

1753
01:01:50,123 --> 01:01:51,541
This is so satisfying.

1754
01:01:52,667 --> 01:01:54,460
Hey, Sang-soon, play us some guitar.

1755
01:01:54,544 --> 01:01:56,587
Should I?

1756
01:01:56,671 --> 01:01:58,589
HE BROUGHT HIS GUITAR
FOR THIS MOMENT

1757
01:01:58,673 --> 01:02:00,758
- Wow, really?
- This is awesome.

1758
01:02:00,842 --> 01:02:02,510
I guess this is what I'm here for.

1759
01:02:06,347 --> 01:02:08,599
I can't believe I'm seeing this in person.

1760
01:02:08,683 --> 01:02:09,851
- I know.
- Incredible.

1761
01:02:10,727 --> 01:02:12,562
PRO MODE ON

1762
01:02:18,192 --> 01:02:19,986
- Oh, "Beach Again"?
- "Beach Again."

1763
01:02:20,069 --> 01:02:22,905
- Oh, wow! Sounds great.
- "Beach Again." Yeah.

1764
01:02:24,157 --> 01:02:26,409
"BEACH AGAIN" IS
A PROJECT GROUP SONG

1765
01:02:26,492 --> 01:02:28,286
BY JAE-SEOK, HYO-RI, AND RAIN,

1766
01:02:28,369 --> 01:02:31,539
COMPOSED BY SANG-SOON
WITH LYRICS BY HYO-RI

1767
01:02:31,622 --> 01:02:32,582
Ah, this is nice.

1768
01:02:33,458 --> 01:02:34,417
"BEACH AGAIN" BY SSAK3

1769
01:02:34,500 --> 01:02:36,210
Everyone, all together.

1770
01:02:37,837 --> 01:02:39,005
<i>My heart </i>

1771
01:02:39,589 --> 01:02:42,592
<i>Is fluttering again </i>

1772
01:02:42,675 --> 01:02:46,888
<i>Being here with you </i>

1773
01:02:46,971 --> 01:02:49,682
<i>Breathing the same air </i>

1774
01:02:49,766 --> 01:02:52,810
<i>In this moment </i>

1775
01:02:52,894 --> 01:02:54,061
<i>I thought I'd never </i>

1776
01:02:55,521 --> 01:02:58,649
<i>See you again </i>

1777
01:02:59,859 --> 01:03:03,738
<i>That you were just a memory </i>

1778
01:03:03,821 --> 01:03:05,490
<i>So I put you away </i>

1779
01:03:05,573 --> 01:03:08,326
<i>Tucked deep inside a drawer </i>

1780
01:03:08,409 --> 01:03:09,994
- <i>Oppa</i>, it's your part.
- Mine?

1781
01:03:10,661 --> 01:03:14,499
<i>As time kept flowing </i>

1782
01:03:14,582 --> 01:03:18,127
<i>The memories of you and me </i>

1783
01:03:18,795 --> 01:03:20,880
<i>Only faded more and more </i>

1784
01:03:21,464 --> 01:03:25,301
<i>I thought it was over </i>

1785
01:03:25,384 --> 01:03:26,260
ONE! TWO!

1786
01:03:26,344 --> 01:03:28,888
<i>Last summer at the beach </i>

1787
01:03:28,971 --> 01:03:30,181
Wait, you want me to sing?

1788
01:03:30,264 --> 01:03:33,643
<i>Just the two of us </i>

1789
01:03:34,811 --> 01:03:36,521
DOESN'T KNOW THE LYRICS,
JUST FEELING IT

1790
01:03:36,604 --> 01:03:39,023
<i>Because I was with you </i>

1791
01:03:39,106 --> 01:03:40,107
<i>I shone even brighter </i>

1792
01:03:40,817 --> 01:03:42,610
<i>And became a star </i>

1793
01:03:43,361 --> 01:03:44,779
Uh, we should start over.

1794
01:03:44,862 --> 01:03:45,780
Let's start over.

1795
01:03:45,863 --> 01:03:46,697
CAN'T HIT HIGH NOTES

1796
01:03:47,448 --> 01:03:49,116
All Min-ju's fault.

1797
01:03:50,326 --> 01:03:52,787
A round of applause!

1798
01:03:54,330 --> 01:03:56,749
THE BONFIRE TIME CONTINUES

1799
01:04:00,127 --> 01:04:01,921
Whoa!

1800
01:04:03,381 --> 01:04:04,841
Oh, that was good.

1801
01:04:04,924 --> 01:04:06,759
THE NIGHT DEEPENS
AROUND A SINGLE FIRE

1802
01:04:09,470 --> 01:04:12,431
All right, so,
it's just about 8:30 right now.

1803
01:04:12,515 --> 01:04:14,100
The night's starting to wind down.

1804
01:04:14,725 --> 01:04:17,728
The fire's still going,
so feel free to enjoy it a bit longer.

1805
01:04:17,812 --> 01:04:19,146
Then, right at 10 o'clock will be…

1806
01:04:19,230 --> 01:04:20,648
- Lights out.
- …lights out.

1807
01:04:20,731 --> 01:04:23,901
And as for tomorrow,
I think you can wake up around 7.

1808
01:04:23,985 --> 01:04:24,861
Sound okay?

1809
01:04:24,944 --> 01:04:26,279
- Yes.
- At seven.

1810
01:04:26,362 --> 01:04:28,155
Now, as we mentioned earlier,

1811
01:04:28,239 --> 01:04:32,076
Director Lee Hyo-ri will graciously
be leading a yoga class in the morning

1812
01:04:32,159 --> 01:04:34,370
for you all, as a special event.

1813
01:04:34,453 --> 01:04:37,415
If you're interested,
you can join her in the quiz room.

1814
01:04:37,498 --> 01:04:39,917
Captains, anything you'd like to say?

1815
01:04:40,001 --> 01:04:41,127
Captain Byeon?

1816
01:04:41,210 --> 01:04:43,504
I hope you are comfortable
for your first night here.

1817
01:04:45,381 --> 01:04:48,050
And I hope this moment
becomes a great memory for you.

1818
01:04:48,759 --> 01:04:50,553
- Aw!
- Good night, yeah.

1819
01:04:51,262 --> 01:04:53,222
Okay, I'm done.

1820
01:04:53,973 --> 01:04:56,684
- Okay, hold on.
- Yeah, I had a great time today.

1821
01:04:56,767 --> 01:04:58,102
COPYING EVERYTHING
WOO-SEOK DOES

1822
01:04:58,185 --> 01:05:00,479
It's such a shame
the day's already coming to an end.

1823
01:05:00,563 --> 01:05:02,982
I hope you all have a warm night.
Thank you.

1824
01:05:03,065 --> 01:05:04,817
It was a lot of fun.

1825
01:05:04,901 --> 01:05:07,486
- All right, thank you!
- Thank you.

1826
01:05:09,363 --> 01:05:11,949
By the way, what did we decide
about sleeping outdoors?

1827
01:05:12,033 --> 01:05:13,492
Oh, that's right.

1828
01:05:14,702 --> 01:05:16,746
NOW IT'S NOVEMBER, THE DAY-NIGHT
TEMPERATURE GAP HAS WIDENED

1829
01:05:16,829 --> 01:05:18,664
CURRENT TEMPERATURE 4ºC

1830
01:05:18,748 --> 01:05:19,790
Aren't you cold?

1831
01:05:19,874 --> 01:05:21,292
Yeah, but I'm okay for now.

1832
01:05:21,375 --> 01:05:22,209
- You're okay?
- Yeah.

1833
01:05:22,293 --> 01:05:23,294
Should I close the doors?

1834
01:05:23,377 --> 01:05:24,712
- It's a bit cold.
- Right. Yeah.

1835
01:05:24,795 --> 01:05:27,298
JAE-SEOK'S BEEN WORRIED
ABOUT THE COLD WEATHER

1836
01:05:27,381 --> 01:05:29,592
I don't think they can
sleep outside tonight.

1837
01:05:29,675 --> 01:05:31,886
By dawn, they'll be frozen stiff.

1838
01:05:33,846 --> 01:05:35,932
I think it's going to be too cold tonight.

1839
01:05:36,015 --> 01:05:37,683
If you can't sleep outside,

1840
01:05:37,767 --> 01:05:41,687
we'll look for another option, like
helping out with breakfast or something.

1841
01:05:41,771 --> 01:05:44,065
TEAM WOO-SEOK'S PENALTY:
BREAKFAST DUTY

1842
01:05:45,316 --> 01:05:47,193
The moon is not even full
and it's so bright.

1843
01:05:47,276 --> 01:05:48,277
Wow!

1844
01:05:48,861 --> 01:05:50,488
It's so pretty. I should make a wish.

1845
01:05:54,659 --> 01:05:56,369
It's not a perfect full moon though.

1846
01:05:56,452 --> 01:05:57,453
PLEASE DON'T LET ME CRY

1847
01:05:57,536 --> 01:05:58,996
Woo-seok, it's not a perfect full moon,

1848
01:05:59,080 --> 01:06:01,457
- so even if you make a wish…
- Oh, I just did it because I wanted to.

1849
01:06:01,540 --> 01:06:02,500
- Yeah, but--
- It doesn't matter

1850
01:06:02,583 --> 01:06:04,293
if it's a perfect full moon or not.
I just…

1851
01:06:05,544 --> 01:06:06,712
Oh, but… I…

1852
01:06:06,796 --> 01:06:08,381
NITPICKING EVERY LITTLE THING
WOO-SEOK DOES

1853
01:06:08,464 --> 01:06:11,592
…I heard you're not supposed
to make a wish on a moon like that.

1854
01:06:11,676 --> 01:06:13,135
- Oh, really?
- It's the law.

1855
01:06:13,636 --> 01:06:15,930
What law?
Is that actually written somewhere?

1856
01:06:16,639 --> 01:06:18,391
- I don't know exactly where.
- Where? Where exactly…

1857
01:06:18,474 --> 01:06:20,643
But I remember hearing that somewhere,
so I thought I'd let you know.

1858
01:06:20,726 --> 01:06:22,895
Can you tell me specifically
where you heard that?

1859
01:06:22,979 --> 01:06:25,064
- Thank you. Good night.
- See you tomorrow.

1860
01:06:25,147 --> 01:06:27,108
- Good night.
- See you tomorrow.

1861
01:06:27,191 --> 01:06:28,567
Thank you. Good night.

1862
01:06:28,651 --> 01:06:30,111
- Good night. Yeah.
- Okay.

1863
01:06:31,195 --> 01:06:35,199
KWANG-SOO & WOO-SEOK DOUSE THE
BONFIRE WITH THE REMAINING GUESTS

1864
01:06:35,866 --> 01:06:37,952
I saw some cereal. I'll have some of that.

1865
01:06:40,621 --> 01:06:41,706
You're hungry now?

1866
01:06:42,248 --> 01:06:44,542
Oh, yeah. Now that I'm feeling better.

1867
01:06:44,625 --> 01:06:46,836
- Hang on. I'll get it for you.
- You're such a mess.

1868
01:06:46,919 --> 01:06:48,796
Or we have some leftover soup.

1869
01:06:48,879 --> 01:06:51,465
- Oh, yeah, I would have that.
- All right, hold on.

1870
01:06:52,049 --> 01:06:53,634
CHECKING IF THERE'S ANY RICE LEFT

1871
01:06:53,718 --> 01:06:55,094
We have a little rice left.

1872
01:06:55,177 --> 01:06:56,345
Looking for food?

1873
01:06:56,429 --> 01:06:57,930
- Sin-jeong didn't eat.
- Yeah.

1874
01:06:58,014 --> 01:07:00,641
Now that she's feeling better,
she's starving all of a sudden.

1875
01:07:00,725 --> 01:07:02,935
That's a relief.
I'm glad you're feeling better.

1876
01:07:03,019 --> 01:07:05,229
Rice and soup? You want some kimchi?

1877
01:07:05,771 --> 01:07:07,106
Yeah.

1878
01:07:07,189 --> 01:07:09,608
You don't really say "no" to things,
do you?

1879
01:07:11,235 --> 01:07:12,820
That's hilarious.

1880
01:07:14,864 --> 01:07:17,116
SERVING UP A NICE, HOT
BOWL OF SOUP

1881
01:07:17,783 --> 01:07:19,869
AND SETTING OUT SOME KIMCHI TOO

1882
01:07:19,952 --> 01:07:21,787
- Thank you so much for the food.
- Sure, enjoy.

1883
01:07:21,871 --> 01:07:23,289
Enjoy.

1884
01:07:24,457 --> 01:07:25,916
- Thank you.
- Good night.

1885
01:07:26,000 --> 01:07:27,960
- See you. Have a good night.
- Thanks so much.

1886
01:07:28,044 --> 01:07:29,920
- See you.
- Enjoy. Good night.

1887
01:07:31,255 --> 01:07:32,214
Hey, great work today.

1888
01:07:32,298 --> 01:07:34,091
- Yeah, you too.
- Yeah, thanks, you too.

1889
01:07:34,717 --> 01:07:35,801
FINALLY, A MOMENT TO BREATHE

1890
01:07:35,885 --> 01:07:36,761
Geez.

1891
01:07:36,844 --> 01:07:38,095
The day's over at last.

1892
01:07:38,929 --> 01:07:40,222
Let's take a look.

1893
01:07:40,306 --> 01:07:41,849
- Oh, Chae-won is the…
- The kid.

1894
01:07:41,932 --> 01:07:44,310
"I want to play the games
I've only seen on TV."

1895
01:07:45,478 --> 01:07:46,395
WISH GRANTED

1896
01:07:46,479 --> 01:07:47,438
Chae-eun.

1897
01:07:47,521 --> 01:07:48,814
NEXT IS HER SISTER CHAE-EUN

1898
01:07:48,898 --> 01:07:50,232
For her captain choice she wrote:

1899
01:07:50,316 --> 01:07:52,610
"Anyone, but the handsome
Woo-seok most of all."

1900
01:07:52,693 --> 01:07:54,361
That's so funny.

1901
01:07:54,445 --> 01:07:55,946
Everyone put down "Byeon Woo-seok."

1902
01:07:56,030 --> 01:07:57,573
- She could've left out the handsome part.
- Everyone.

1903
01:07:57,656 --> 01:08:00,117
Here. For the food
she wants to eat, Hye-jeong wrote,

1904
01:08:00,201 --> 01:08:03,496
"Anything Woo-seok makes,
or the thick-cut samgyeopsal."

1905
01:08:04,288 --> 01:08:05,206
Oh, my goodness.

1906
01:08:05,289 --> 01:08:06,499
CAPTAIN BYEON IS
ESPECIALLY POPULAR

1907
01:08:07,083 --> 01:08:08,542
Wow, all Nam-jin wrote

1908
01:08:08,626 --> 01:08:10,461
is he wants to make memories
with his brother.

1909
01:08:10,544 --> 01:08:12,296
- There's nothing else he wants to do.
- Wow.

1910
01:08:13,422 --> 01:08:15,716
DONE CHECKING
ALL REGISTRATION FORMS

1911
01:08:15,800 --> 01:08:18,385
First of all, great work today, guys.

1912
01:08:18,469 --> 01:08:21,180
Tomorrow, we'll make porridge
with Sang-soon and Hyo-ri,

1913
01:08:21,263 --> 01:08:23,265
and some toast for breakfast.

1914
01:08:23,349 --> 01:08:24,975
You said you wanted to make a salad too

1915
01:08:25,059 --> 01:08:27,436
- with persimmons and apples?
- Ah, sounds great.

1916
01:08:27,520 --> 01:08:30,731
Wait, Sang-soon. Tomorrow morning,
you said you'd make coffee.

1917
01:08:30,815 --> 01:08:32,233
Mmm. Oh, yeah, right.

1918
01:08:32,316 --> 01:08:33,859
- The coffee.
- But then he'll have to make

1919
01:08:33,943 --> 01:08:36,112
the salad, the porridge and the coffee,

1920
01:08:36,195 --> 01:08:38,239
so we should take one of those
off his plate.

1921
01:08:38,322 --> 01:08:40,116
Peeling and cutting the persimmons,

1922
01:08:40,199 --> 01:08:42,910
getting the tangerines ready,
slicing up all the apples.

1923
01:08:42,993 --> 01:08:44,829
- Oh, yeah.
- Maybe you guys could assist me.

1924
01:08:44,912 --> 01:08:46,372
- We'll just do whatever he tells us to do.
- Yeah.

1925
01:08:46,455 --> 01:08:48,582
Just tell us what needs to be done,
and we'll handle it.

1926
01:08:48,666 --> 01:08:49,667
- Yeah.
- Okay.

1927
01:08:49,750 --> 01:08:51,335
- Let's get some rest now.
- Yeah, yeah.

1928
01:08:51,418 --> 01:08:53,254
